class="article_hero-underline__eXN8a"/><div class="authorDate_author__zLtCV" data-test="author"><span class="authorDate_author__prefix__fYlx5">by<!-- --> </span><span class="authorDate_author__name__zLIHO" data-test="author-name">Team Empire</span><span> <!-- -->|<!-- --> </span><div class="authorDate_author__date__uYP2E" data-test="author-date"><span class="authorDate_author__modifiedAt__8VGNX">Posted on</span><time datetime="23-01-2023">23 01 2023</time></div></div><div class="article_article-content__l3M2F false"><span class="content_content__ibcyj" data-test="content">
<p>Its a big question: what are the best movies of all time? And its one with many answers  there are all kinds of reasons why the greatest films ever made endure in the way they do. They create unforgettable images, conjure overwhelming emotions, craft thrilling stories, and deliver characters who leap off the screen. Theres astonishing technical mastery that brings those stories to life, plots that twist and turn in all kinds of unexpected ways, performances that help us fall head-over-heels for people who dont exist, and transcendent experiences that change our heads and hearts. The best films  from classic movies that have stood the test of time, to contemporary works that changed the game  offer heartwarming comfort, iconic scares, big laughs, and pulse-pounding suspense, becoming firm audience favourites and garnering critical acclaim.</p>
</span><span class="content_content__ibcyj" data-test="content">
<p>In creating a list of the 100 best movies of all time, <em>Empire</em> asked readers to share their picks  a selection of movies that comfort, challenge, and pioneer. Films that blow your mind, help you see things from a new perspective, and that continue to shape cinema as we know it today. Films that make you <em>feel</em> something. Combining reader votes with critics choices from Team Empire, here we have it  read it in full below.</p>
</span><span class="content_content__ibcyj" data-test="content">
<p>Looking for our list of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/features/best-tv-shows-ever-2/" target="_blank">The 100 Greatest TV Shows Of All Time? Read here</a>.</p>

class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">1<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">100) Reservoir Dogs</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/quentin-tarantino/" target="_blank">Quentin Tarantino</a>'s terrific twist on the heist-gone-wrong thriller ricochets the zing and fizz of its dialogue around a gloriously intense single setting (for the most part) and centres the majority of its action around one long and incredibly bloody death scene. Oh, and by the way: Nice Guy Eddie was shot by Mr. White. Who fired twice. Case closed.</p>

class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-1"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Groundhog Day" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5761/f590/5edf/a806/4660/IMG_0301.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">2<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">99) Groundhog Day</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/bill-murray/" target="_blank">Bill Murray</a> at the height of his loveable (eventually) schmuck powers. <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/andie-macdowell/" target="_blank">Andie McDowell</a> bringing the brains and the heart. And <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/harold-ramis/" target="_blank">Harold Ramis</a> (directing and co-writing with Danny Rubin) managing to find gold in the story of a man trapped in a time loop. It might not have been the first to tap this particular trope, but it's head and shoulders above the rest. Murray's snarktastic delivery makes the early going easy to laugh at, but as the movie finds deeper things to say about existence and morals, it never feels like a polemic.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/groundhog-day-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Groundhog Day</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-01"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-2"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Paddington 2" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/590a/f590/5e6f/8a06/4673/IMG_0300.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/590a/f590/5e6f/8a06/4673/IMG_0300.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/590a/f590/5e6f/8a06/4673/IMG_0300.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/590a/f590/5e6f/8a06/4673/IMG_0300.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/590a/f590/5e6f/8a06/4673/IMG_0300.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/590a/f590/5e6f/8a06/4673/IMG_0300.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">3<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">98) Paddington 2</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>When the first <em>Paddington</em> was on the way, early trailers didn't look entirely promising. Yet co-writer/director <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/paul-king/" target="_blank">Paul King</a> delivered a truly wonderful film bursting with joy, imagination, kindness and just one or two hard stares. How was he going to follow that? Turns out, with more of the same, but also plenty of fresh pleasures. Paddington (bouncily voiced by <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/ben-whishaw/" target="_blank">Ben Whishaw</a>) matches wits with washed-up actor Phoenix Buchanan (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/hugh-grant/" target="_blank">Hugh Grant</a>, chewing scenery like fine steak), being framed for theft and getting sent to prison. Like all great sequels, it works superbly as a double bill with the original.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/paddington-2-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Paddington 2</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-3"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Amelie" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5a19/5165/432a/703b/7912/IMG_0299.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5a19/5165/432a/703b/7912/IMG_0299.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5a19/5165/432a/703b/7912/IMG_0299.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5a19/5165/432a/703b/7912/IMG_0299.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5a19/5165/432a/703b/7912/IMG_0299.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5a19/5165/432a/703b/7912/IMG_0299.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">4<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">97) Amelie</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jean-pierre-jeunet/" target="_blank">Jean-Pierre Jeunet</a>'s beautifully whimsical Parisian rom-com succeeded not only because he found the perfect lead in <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/audrey-tautou/" target="_blank">Audrey Tautou</a>, but also because his numerous surreal touches truly gave a sense that there is always magic in the world around us  if we only know how to look for it.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/amelie-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Amelie</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-02"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-4"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Brokeback Mountain" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5af1/dbee/af61/2a68/fd95/IMG_0298.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5af1/dbee/af61/2a68/fd95/IMG_0298.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5af1/dbee/af61/2a68/fd95/IMG_0298.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5af1/dbee/af61/2a68/fd95/IMG_0298.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5af1/dbee/af61/2a68/fd95/IMG_0298.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5af1/dbee/af61/2a68/fd95/IMG_0298.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">5<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">96) Brokeback Mountain</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/ang-lee/" target="_blank">Ang Lee</a> adapts Annie Proulx's short story (with <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/larry-mcmurtry/" target="_blank">Larry McMurtry</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/diana-ossana/" target="_blank">Diana Ossana</a> on script duty) with sensitivity, grace, and differing scope  the intimacy of the relationship between <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jake-gyllenhaal/" target="_blank">Jake Gyllenhaal</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/heath-ledger/" target="_blank">Heath Ledger</a>'s shepherds backed by beautiful mountain landscapes. The love between Ennis Del Mar (Ledger) and Jack Twist (Gyllenhaal) is complicated by the mores of the time and their need to marry their respective girlfriends. It'll break your heart and offer hope all at the same time, and the film ended up scoring Best Adapted Screenplay, Music and Directing Oscars.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/brokeback-mountain-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Brokeback Mountain</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-5"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Donnie Darko" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5c11/dbee/afc5/5968/fda3/IMG_0297.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5c11/dbee/afc5/5968/fda3/IMG_0297.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5c11/dbee/afc5/5968/fda3/IMG_0297.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5c11/dbee/afc5/5968/fda3/IMG_0297.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5c11/dbee/afc5/5968/fda3/IMG_0297.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5c11/dbee/afc5/5968/fda3/IMG_0297.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">6<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">95) Donnie Darko</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/richard-kelly/" target="_blank">Richard Kelly</a>'s time-looping, sci-fi-horror-blending high-school movie is the very definition of a cult classic. It was a struggle to get made, it flopped on release, then found its crowd via word-of-mouth and a palpable sense that its creator really, you know, gets it. And let's not forget how goddamn funny it is, too.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/donnie-darko-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Donnie Darko</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-03"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-6"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Scott Pilgrim Vs. The World" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5caa/5909/d042/bd4c/85f9/IMG_0296.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5caa/5909/d042/bd4c/85f9/IMG_0296.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5caa/5909/d042/bd4c/85f9/IMG_0296.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5caa/5909/d042/bd4c/85f9/IMG_0296.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5caa/5909/d042/bd4c/85f9/IMG_0296.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5caa/5909/d042/bd4c/85f9/IMG_0296.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">7<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">94) Scott Pilgrim Vs. The World</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>With <em>Scott Pilgrim Vs. The World</em>, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/edgar-wright/" target="_blank">Edgar Wright</a> leaned all the way in to the things that make his directorial style so singular  excellent needle drops, a bold colour palette, whip-pans and whip-smart wit alike. <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/michael-cera/" target="_blank">Michael Cera</a> is the put-upon protagonist, but it's Ramona's (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/mary-elizabeth-winstead/" target="_blank">Mary Elizabeth Winstead</a>) seven deadly exes that set the screen alight, including <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/chris-evans/" target="_blank">Chris Evans</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/brie-larson/" target="_blank">Brie Larson</a>  before they were saving half the universe together. With masterful touches of magical realism and stunning shots that stick in the mind throughout, <em>Scott Pilgrim</em> is one of Wright's most memorable.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/scott-pilgrim-vs-world-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Scott Pilgrim</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-7"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Portrait Of A Lady On Fire" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5ddd/f590/5ef7/2c06/46a5/IMG_0295.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5ddd/f590/5ef7/2c06/46a5/IMG_0295.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5ddd/f590/5ef7/2c06/46a5/IMG_0295.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5ddd/f590/5ef7/2c06/46a5/IMG_0295.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5ddd/f590/5ef7/2c06/46a5/IMG_0295.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5ddd/f590/5ef7/2c06/46a5/IMG_0295.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">8<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">93) Portrait Of A Lady On Fire</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/celine-sciamma/" target="_blank">Celine Sciamma</a>'s magnetic, masterful lesbian romance may be a recent addition to this list, but became an instant landmark of queer cinema upon its release. Starring <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/noemie-merlant/" target="_blank">Noumie Merlant</a> as an 18th century painter and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/adele-haenel/" target="_blank">Aduele Haenel</a> as her elusive subject, <em>Portrait Of A Lady On Fire</em> is a tale of an epic love developed in the quietest, most delicate way, formed in stolen moments and glances. Sciamma's carefully constructed script is matched by Claire Mathon's cinematography, each shot like a Renaissance painting brought to life. Pure poetry.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/portrait-of-a-lady-on-fire/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Portrait Of A Lady On Fire</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-04"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-8"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Lu00e9on" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5ed4/5165/4393/173b/793d/IMG_0294.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5ed4/5165/4393/173b/793d/IMG_0294.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5ed4/5165/4393/173b/793d/IMG_0294.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5ed4/5165/4393/173b/793d/IMG_0294.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5ed4/5165/4393/173b/793d/IMG_0294.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/5ed4/5165/4393/173b/793d/IMG_0294.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">9<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">92) Lon</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>In some ways, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/luc-besson/" target="_blank">Luc Besson</a>'s first English-language movie is a spiritual spin-off: after all, isn't <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jean-reno/" target="_blank">Jean Reno</a>'s eponymous hitman just Nikita's Victor The Cleaner renamed and fleshed out? Of course, its greatest strength is in <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/natalie-portman/" target="_blank">Natalie Portman</a>, delivering a luminous, career-creating performance as vengeful 12-year-old Mathilda, whose relationship with the monosyllabic killer is truly affecting, and nimbly stays just on the right side of acceptable.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/leon-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Lon</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-9"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Logan" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7202/dbee/af4f/0d68/fe72/IMG_0293.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7202/dbee/af4f/0d68/fe72/IMG_0293.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7202/dbee/af4f/0d68/fe72/IMG_0293.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7202/dbee/af4f/0d68/fe72/IMG_0293.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7202/dbee/af4f/0d68/fe72/IMG_0293.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7202/dbee/af4f/0d68/fe72/IMG_0293.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">10<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">91) Logan</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>If you're going to wrap up your tenure as one of the most loved superhero icons in fiction, it's hard to think of a better way than how <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/hugh-jackman/" target="_blank">Hugh Jackman</a>  with <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/james-mangold/" target="_blank">James Mangold</a> directing  punched out on the time clock of playing Wolverine. Set in a dark near-future world where an aging Logan is caring for a mentally unstable Professor Xavier (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/patrick-stewart/" target="_blank">Patrick Stewart</a>) and getting mixed up yet again with some very dangerous people , <em>Logan</em> is a truly original superhero tale that is mournful without being morbid. It's so outside the established mold, in fact, it's honestly a wonder the film ever got made.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/logan-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Logan</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-05"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-10"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Terminator" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/72d1/5909/d00e/394c/86c8/IMG_0292.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/72d1/5909/d00e/394c/86c8/IMG_0292.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/72d1/5909/d00e/394c/86c8/IMG_0292.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/72d1/5909/d00e/394c/86c8/IMG_0292.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/72d1/5909/d00e/394c/86c8/IMG_0292.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/72d1/5909/d00e/394c/86c8/IMG_0292.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">11<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">90) The Terminator</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>It features time travel and a cyborg, with car chases and shoot-outs, but in <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/james-cameron/" target="_blank">James Cameron</a>'s first proper movie (ie. not featuring flying piranhas) it's all packed around the blood-covered endoskeleton of a relentless-killer horror pic. After all, what is <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/arnold-schwarzenegger/" target="_blank">Arnold Schwarzenegger</a>'s Uzi-9mm-toting Terminator, if not an upgraded version of <em>Halloween</em>'s Michael Myers?</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/terminator-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Terminator</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-11"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="No Country For Old Men" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/73a4/dbee/afcc/7468/fe86/IMG_0291.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/73a4/dbee/afcc/7468/fe86/IMG_0291.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/73a4/dbee/afcc/7468/fe86/IMG_0291.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/73a4/dbee/afcc/7468/fe86/IMG_0291.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/73a4/dbee/afcc/7468/fe86/IMG_0291.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/73a4/dbee/afcc/7468/fe86/IMG_0291.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">12<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">89) No Country For Old Men</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>The Coen brothers' <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/cormac-mccarthy/" target="_blank">Cormac McCarthy</a> adaptation is a tension-ratcheting, 1980 Texas-set chase movie, which also thoughtfully considers the question: how can good people ever possibly deal with a world going to shit? It also revealed that <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/javier-bardem/" target="_blank">Javier Bardem</a> makes an awesome villain; ever since he played <em>No Country</em>'s cold-blooded assassin Anton Chigurh, Hollywood can't stop making him the bad guy.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/country-old-men-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of No Country For Old Men</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-06"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-12"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Titanic" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7484/3ebe/47c9/9c9c/e22c/IMG_0290.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7484/3ebe/47c9/9c9c/e22c/IMG_0290.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7484/3ebe/47c9/9c9c/e22c/IMG_0290.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7484/3ebe/47c9/9c9c/e22c/IMG_0290.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7484/3ebe/47c9/9c9c/e22c/IMG_0290.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7484/3ebe/47c9/9c9c/e22c/IMG_0290.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">13<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">88) Titanic</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/james-cameron/" target="_blank">James Cameron</a> doesn't do things by halves. His movie about the 1912 sinking of the world's biggest cruise liner was the most expensive ever made, suffered a difficult, overrunning shoot, and was predicted to be a career-ending flop. But it turned out to be one of the most successful films of all time (in terms of both box office and Awards), and made him King Of The World.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/titanic-2-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Titanic</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-13"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Exorcist" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7584/3ebe/474f/b09c/e235/IMG_0289.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7584/3ebe/474f/b09c/e235/IMG_0289.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7584/3ebe/474f/b09c/e235/IMG_0289.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7584/3ebe/474f/b09c/e235/IMG_0289.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7584/3ebe/474f/b09c/e235/IMG_0289.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7584/3ebe/474f/b09c/e235/IMG_0289.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">14<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">87) The Exorcist</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/william-friedkin/" target="_blank">William Friedkin</a>'s horror masterwork, in which a 12-year-old girl is possessed by a demon, has a reputation as a shocker (in the good sense), with the pea-soup vomit, head-spin and crucifix abuse moments the most regularly cited. But the reason it chills so deeply is the way it sustains and builds its disquieting atmosphere so craftily and consistently throughout.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/exorcist-director-cut-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Exorcist</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-07"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-14"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Black Panther" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7604/5909/d02b/0a4c/86e1/IMG_0288.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7604/5909/d02b/0a4c/86e1/IMG_0288.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7604/5909/d02b/0a4c/86e1/IMG_0288.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7604/5909/d02b/0a4c/86e1/IMG_0288.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7604/5909/d02b/0a4c/86e1/IMG_0288.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7604/5909/d02b/0a4c/86e1/IMG_0288.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">15<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">86) Black Panther</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>After his standout introduction in <em>Captain America: Civil War</em>, 2018's <em>Black Panther</em> allowed us to properly meet <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/chadwick-boseman/" target="_blank">Chadwick Boseman</a>'s T'Challa, and see his Wakandan kingdom in all its glory. Impeccably directed by <em>Creed</em>'s <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/ryan-coogler/" target="_blank">Ryan Coogler</a>, it's an Afrofuturistic vision oozing with cool, colourful regality, expressed through its Oscar-winning costume design, stunning set pieces and thrumming soundtrack. Soaring to billion dollar-plus box office takings, Black Panther's cultural impact cannot be understated  and after the tragic loss of Boseman in 2020, the film lives on as the defining role for a truly remarkable talent.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/black-panther-review-2/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Black Panther</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-15"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Shaun Of The Dead" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/76a9/3ebe/47fc/719c/e242/IMG_0286.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/76a9/3ebe/47fc/719c/e242/IMG_0286.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/76a9/3ebe/47fc/719c/e242/IMG_0286.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/76a9/3ebe/47fc/719c/e242/IMG_0286.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/76a9/3ebe/47fc/719c/e242/IMG_0286.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/76a9/3ebe/47fc/719c/e242/IMG_0286.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">16<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">85) Shaun Of The Dead</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Before its release, you might have been forgiven for thinking it would be <em>Spaced: The Movie</em>. But <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/edgar-wright/" target="_blank">Edgar Wright</a>, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/simon-pegg/" target="_blank">Simon Pegg</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/nick-frost/" target="_blank">Nick Frost</a>'s first feature is genuinely stand-alone: a savvy blend of proper-funny comedy and seriously gruesome undead-horror which, funnily enough, played a big part in the zombie-movie resurgence we're still enjoying now.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/shaun-dead-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Shaun Of The Dead</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-08"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-16"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Lost In Translation" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/785c/dbee/afdb/9068/fead/IMG_0285.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/785c/dbee/afdb/9068/fead/IMG_0285.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/785c/dbee/afdb/9068/fead/IMG_0285.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/785c/dbee/afdb/9068/fead/IMG_0285.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/785c/dbee/afdb/9068/fead/IMG_0285.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/785c/dbee/afdb/9068/fead/IMG_0285.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">17<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">84) Lost In Translation</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/sofia-coppola/" target="_blank">Sofia Coppola</a>'s second film is the ultimate jet lag movie, locating its central almost-romance between listless college grad <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/scarlett-johansson/" target="_blank">Scarlett Johansson</a> and life-worn actor <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/bill-murray/" target="_blank">Bill Murray</a> amid the woozy, daydreamy bewilderment of being in a very foreign country and a very different time zone. And it's exactly right that we still don't know what he whispered to her at the end.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/lost-translation-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Lost In Translation</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-17"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Thor: Ragnarok" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/791c/5165/4341/f63b/7a3b/IMG_0284.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/791c/5165/4341/f63b/7a3b/IMG_0284.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/791c/5165/4341/f63b/7a3b/IMG_0284.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/791c/5165/4341/f63b/7a3b/IMG_0284.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/791c/5165/4341/f63b/7a3b/IMG_0284.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/791c/5165/4341/f63b/7a3b/IMG_0284.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">18<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">83) Thor: Ragnarok</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Marvel has cannily employed directors who have more usually made smaller, indie movies, handed them the keys to the giant machine that is their cinematic universe and (within reason) let them do their thing. Among the best to grasp that opportunity is <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/taika-waititi/" target="_blank">Taika Waititi</a>, who helped find Thor's true funny bone, a more effective weapon than Mjolnir. <em>Ragnarok</em>, which shakes up Thor's entire world (by, er, destroying it) is a hilarious take on a superhero story, full of action, while re-introducing <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/mark-ruffalo/" target="_blank">Mark Ruffalo</a>'s Hulk in fantastic fashion and having us meet the likes of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/tessa-thompson/" target="_blank">Tessa Thompson'</a>s Valkyrie and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jeff-goldblum/" target="_blank">Jeff Goldblum</a>'s Grandmaster.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/thor-ragnarok-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Thor: Ragnarok</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-09"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-18"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Usual Suspects" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/79e7/5165/4337/0a3b/7a44/IMG_0283.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/79e7/5165/4337/0a3b/7a44/IMG_0283.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/79e7/5165/4337/0a3b/7a44/IMG_0283.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/79e7/5165/4337/0a3b/7a44/IMG_0283.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/79e7/5165/4337/0a3b/7a44/IMG_0283.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/79e7/5165/4337/0a3b/7a44/IMG_0283.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">19<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">82) The Usual Suspects</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>While the line-up team-up is a great concept, director <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/bryan-singer/" target="_blank">Bryan Singer</a> and writer <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/christopher-mcquarrie/" target="_blank">Christopher McQuarrie</a>'s super-twisted, uber-cool crime thriller attains true greatness through its supernatural-horror-style backdrop, conjuring a phantom menace "Keyser Soze" who terrifies even the most hardened criminal.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/usual-suspects-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Usual Suspects</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-19"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Psycho" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7abf/3ebe/4795/339c/e267/IMG_0282.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7abf/3ebe/4795/339c/e267/IMG_0282.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7abf/3ebe/4795/339c/e267/IMG_0282.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7abf/3ebe/4795/339c/e267/IMG_0282.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7abf/3ebe/4795/339c/e267/IMG_0282.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7abf/3ebe/4795/339c/e267/IMG_0282.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">20<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">81) Psycho</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>The movie Universal originally didn't want <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/alfred-hitchcock/" target="_blank">Hitchcock</a> to make not only turned out to be a hands-down masterpiece but also effectively invented a genre: the psycho-killer slasher movie. No longer were movie monsters just big, hairy wolf-men, or vampires, or swampy fish-things. They could now look completely normal. They could be the guy sat right next to you, in fact...</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/psycho-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Psycho</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-10"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-20"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="L.A. Confidential" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7b55/dbee/afab/a168/febc/IMG_0280.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7b55/dbee/afab/a168/febc/IMG_0280.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7b55/dbee/afab/a168/febc/IMG_0280.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7b55/dbee/afab/a168/febc/IMG_0280.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7b55/dbee/afab/a168/febc/IMG_0280.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7b55/dbee/afab/a168/febc/IMG_0280.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">21<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">80) L.A. Confidential</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Twenty years on, and still nobody's made a better <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/james-ellroy/" target="_blank">James Ellroy</a> adaptation than <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/curtis-hanson/" target="_blank">Curtis Hanson</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/brian-helgeland/" target="_blank">Brian Helgeland</a>'s boldly streamlined take on the heavy-plotted third novel in Ellroy's 'L.A. Quartet'. Its spot-on casting hardly hurt, including <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/russell-crowe/" target="_blank">Russell Crowe</a> as conscience-discovering bruiser Bud White and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/guy-pearce/" target="_blank">Guy Pearce</a> as ramrod rookie Ed Exley.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/l-confidential-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of L.A. Confidential</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-21"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="E.T.  The Extra Terrestrial" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7c42/f590/5e2d/0306/47b8/IMG_0279.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7c42/f590/5e2d/0306/47b8/IMG_0279.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7c42/f590/5e2d/0306/47b8/IMG_0279.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7c42/f590/5e2d/0306/47b8/IMG_0279.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7c42/f590/5e2d/0306/47b8/IMG_0279.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7c42/f590/5e2d/0306/47b8/IMG_0279.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">22<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">79) E.T.  The Extra Terrestrial</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>With the "Amblin" style so regularly referenced these days (most successfully in the Duffer brothers' <em>Stranger Things</em>), it's worth reminding ourselves that it was never more perfectly encapsulated than in <em>E.T</em>.: a children's adventure which carefully beds its supernatural elements in an utterly relatable everykid world, and tempers its cuter, more sentimental moments with a true sense of jeopardy.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/et-extra-terrestrial-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of E.T.</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-11"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-22"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="In The Mood For Love" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7c9b/dbee/af0d/9568/fec4/IMG_0278.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7c9b/dbee/af0d/9568/fec4/IMG_0278.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7c9b/dbee/af0d/9568/fec4/IMG_0278.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7c9b/dbee/af0d/9568/fec4/IMG_0278.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7c9b/dbee/af0d/9568/fec4/IMG_0278.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7c9b/dbee/af0d/9568/fec4/IMG_0278.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">23<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">78) In The Mood For Love</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Years before battling Shang-Chi in the MCU, Hong Kong acting legend <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/tony-leung/" target="_blank">Tony Leung</a> was director <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/wong-kar-wai/" target="_blank">Wong Kar-wai</a>'s greatest muse in gorgeous, simmering masterpieces like <em>Chungking Express</em>, <em>Happy Together</em>  and this remarkable romance, perhaps their greatest collaboration. Leung plays a journalist renting an apartment in 1960s Hong Kong; his neighbour, played by Maggie Cheung, appears as lonely and lost as he is. It soon emerges their spouses are having an affair, and a romance of stolen glances and intimate longing begins to emerge. Love stories are rarely as ravishingly beautiful (or deeply influential) as this.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/mood-love-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of In The Mood For Love</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-23"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Star Wars: Return Of The Jedi" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7d68/5909/d0c9/364c/8722/IMG_0277.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7d68/5909/d0c9/364c/8722/IMG_0277.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7d68/5909/d0c9/364c/8722/IMG_0277.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7d68/5909/d0c9/364c/8722/IMG_0277.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7d68/5909/d0c9/364c/8722/IMG_0277.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7d68/5909/d0c9/364c/8722/IMG_0277.JPG?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">24<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">77) Star Wars: Return Of The Jedi</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>In this post-<em>Phantom Menace</em> world, the Ewoks don't seem quite so egregious, do they? Endor's teddy-bear guerillas might have got sneered at, but they shouldn't blind us to Jedi's assets: the explosive team-re-gathering opening; the crazily high-speed forest chase; and that marvellously edited three-way climactic battle that dextrously flipped us between lightsabers, spaceships and a ferocious (albeit fuzzy) forest conflict.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/star-wars-episode-vi-return-jedi-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Return Of The Jedi</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-12"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-24"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Arrival" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7df7/3ebe/4778/9b9c/e284/IMG_0276.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7df7/3ebe/4778/9b9c/e284/IMG_0276.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7df7/3ebe/4778/9b9c/e284/IMG_0276.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7df7/3ebe/4778/9b9c/e284/IMG_0276.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7df7/3ebe/4778/9b9c/e284/IMG_0276.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/7df7/3ebe/4778/9b9c/e284/IMG_0276.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">25<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">76) Arrival</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/denis-villeneuve/" target="_blank">Denis Villeneuve</a>'s empathic, perception-bending alien visitation drama is a delicately crafted modern rework of <em>The Day The Earth Stood Still</em>, except the extra-terrestrials are truly otherworldly and there's the sky-high obstacle that is the language barrier. With its message that open-minded communication enables us to realise the things we have in common with those who appear vastly different, it feels like genuinely compulsive viewing for these troubled times.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/arrival-2-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Arrival</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-25"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="A Quiet Place" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8191/3ebe/4762/8f9c/e2aa/IMG_0275.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8191/3ebe/4762/8f9c/e2aa/IMG_0275.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8191/3ebe/4762/8f9c/e2aa/IMG_0275.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8191/3ebe/4762/8f9c/e2aa/IMG_0275.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8191/3ebe/4762/8f9c/e2aa/IMG_0275.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8191/3ebe/4762/8f9c/e2aa/IMG_0275.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">26<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">75) A Quiet Place</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Take a simple concept (don't make a sound, or aliens will get you), a stellar cast (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/emily-blunt/" target="_blank">Emily Blunt</a>, Millicent Simmonds, Noah Jupe) and a director with a laser-sharp vision (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/john-krasinski/" target="_blank">John Krasinski</a>) and what do you get? As it turns out, one of the most innovative, refreshing, unbearably tense horror movies of the 21st century. From the second it starts, the imposed silence of <em>A Quiet Place</em> makes it a revelatory cinematic experience  as the Abbott family pad gently around their home, the store, the woods, you feel in your bones that one wrong step equals disaster. The (loudly) ticking time bomb of imminent childbirth sets the scene for a stellar scary finale, but it's the deeply endearing family dynamic that sets this apart.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/quiet-place-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of A Quiet Place</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-13"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-26"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Trainspotting" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/825d/dbee/afae/3e68/feee/IMG_0274.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/825d/dbee/afae/3e68/feee/IMG_0274.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/825d/dbee/afae/3e68/feee/IMG_0274.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/825d/dbee/afae/3e68/feee/IMG_0274.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/825d/dbee/afae/3e68/feee/IMG_0274.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/825d/dbee/afae/3e68/feee/IMG_0274.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">27<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">74) Trainspotting</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>For their follow up to the superb <em>Shallow Grave</em>, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/danny-boyle/" target="_blank">Danny Boyle</a> (director), <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/andrew-macdonald/" target="_blank">Andrew Macdonald</a> (producer) and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/john-hodge/" target="_blank">John Hodge</a> (screenwriter) foolhardily elected to film the supposedly unfilmable: <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/irvine-welsh/" target="_blank">Irvine Welsh</a>'s scrappy, episodic, multi-perspective novel about Edinburgh low-lives. The result couldn't have been more triumphant: the cinematic incarnation of 'Cool Britannia' came with a kick-ass soundtrack, and despite some dark subject matter, came with a punch-the-air uplifting pay-off.</p>
<p><a href="http://empireonline.com/movies/reviews/trainspotting-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Trainspotting</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-27"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Mulholland Drive" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8312/3ebe/47ea/0f9c/e2b5/IMG_0273.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8312/3ebe/47ea/0f9c/e2b5/IMG_0273.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8312/3ebe/47ea/0f9c/e2b5/IMG_0273.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8312/3ebe/47ea/0f9c/e2b5/IMG_0273.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8312/3ebe/47ea/0f9c/e2b5/IMG_0273.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8312/3ebe/47ea/0f9c/e2b5/IMG_0273.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">28<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">73) Mulholland Drive</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/david-lynch/" target="_blank">David Lynch</a> messes with Hollywood itself in a mystery tale that's as twisted as the road it's named after, while presenting Tinseltown as both Dream Factory and a realm of Nightmares. It also put <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/naomi-watts/" target="_blank">Naomi Watts</a> on the map; her audition scene remains as stunning as it was 20 years ago.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/mulholland-drive-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Mulholland Drive</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-14"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-28"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Rear Window" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8412/f590/5eb0/3206/47f2/IMG_0272.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8412/f590/5eb0/3206/47f2/IMG_0272.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8412/f590/5eb0/3206/47f2/IMG_0272.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8412/f590/5eb0/3206/47f2/IMG_0272.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8412/f590/5eb0/3206/47f2/IMG_0272.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8412/f590/5eb0/3206/47f2/IMG_0272.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">29<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">72) Rear Window</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Photographer LB Jeffries (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/james-stewart/" target="_blank">James Stewart</a>) is on sick leave, with a broken leg. He's bored to tears, so he starts spying on his neighbours. Then he witnesses a murder. OR DOES HE? <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/alfred-hitchcock/" target="_blank">Alfred Hitchcock</a> really knew how to take a corker of a premise and spin it into a peerless thriller (that's why they called him The Master Of Suspense), but <em>Rear Window</em> also deserves praise for an astonishing set build: that entire Greenwich Village courtyard was constructed at Paramount Studios, complete with a drainage system that could handle all the rain.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/rear-window-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Rear Window</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-29"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Up" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/84db/3ebe/47eb/e69c/e2c2/IMG_0271.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/84db/3ebe/47eb/e69c/e2c2/IMG_0271.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/84db/3ebe/47eb/e69c/e2c2/IMG_0271.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/84db/3ebe/47eb/e69c/e2c2/IMG_0271.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/84db/3ebe/47eb/e69c/e2c2/IMG_0271.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/84db/3ebe/47eb/e69c/e2c2/IMG_0271.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">30<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">71) Up</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>A lot has been said about the opening to <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/pete-docter/" target="_blank">Pete Docter</a>'s Pixar masterpiece, and rightly so, wringing tears from the hardest of hearts with a wordless sequence set to <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/michael-giacchino/" target="_blank">Michael Giacchino</a>'s lovely, Oscar-winning score that charts the ups and downs of a couple's marriage. Yet while the majority of the film is more of a straight-ahead adventure tale (albeit one with a wacky bird and talking dogs), that doesn't make it any less satisfying. And let's be honest  the story of a man who uses balloons to float his house to a foreign land, accidentally picking up a young wilderness explorer scout as he does, feels perfectly Pixar.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/movie-2-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Up</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-15"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-30"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Spider-Man: Into The Spider-Verse" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/857e/5909/d0db/e74c/8768/IMG_0270.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/857e/5909/d0db/e74c/8768/IMG_0270.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/857e/5909/d0db/e74c/8768/IMG_0270.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/857e/5909/d0db/e74c/8768/IMG_0270.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/857e/5909/d0db/e74c/8768/IMG_0270.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/857e/5909/d0db/e74c/8768/IMG_0270.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">31<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">70) Spider-Man: Into The Spider-Verse</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
