<p>Having <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/phil-lord/" target="_blank">Phil Lord</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/chris-miller/" target="_blank">Chris Miller</a>'s names on a movie is regularly the guarantee of something great, but the full team behind this animated marvel (in both upper- and lower-case senses of the word) is what makes it work. <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/bob-persichetti/" target="_blank">Bob Persichetti</a>, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/peter-ramsey/" target="_blank">Peter Ramsey</a>, and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/rodney-rothman/" target="_blank">Rodney Rothman</a> all added something as directors (with Rothman co-writing alongside Lord) and their animators whipped up a visually dynamic, exciting, and heartwarming adventure that literally spans multiverses before the MCU introduced it. Bringing Miles Morales to the screen was a masterstroke, and <a href="http:///people/shameik-moore/" rel="noopener">Shameik Moore</a>'s vocal work gives him buckets of charm.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/spider-man-spider-verse-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Spider-Man: Into The Spider-Verse</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-31"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Inglourious Basterds" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/86bb/dbee/af72/ce68/ff1c/IMG_0269.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/86bb/dbee/af72/ce68/ff1c/IMG_0269.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/86bb/dbee/af72/ce68/ff1c/IMG_0269.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/86bb/dbee/af72/ce68/ff1c/IMG_0269.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/86bb/dbee/af72/ce68/ff1c/IMG_0269.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/86bb/dbee/af72/ce68/ff1c/IMG_0269.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">32<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">69) Inglourious Basterds</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>From its Sergio Leone-riffing opening to its insanely OTT, history-rewriting finale, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/quentin-tarantino/" target="_blank">Tarantino'</a>s World War II caper never once fails to surprise and entertain. As ever, though, QT's at his best in claustrophobic situations, with the tavern scene ramping up the tension to almost unbearable levels.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/inglourious-basterds-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Inglourious Basterds</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-16"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-32"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Lady Bird" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/874f/3ebe/4715/069c/e2d3/IMG_0268.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/874f/3ebe/4715/069c/e2d3/IMG_0268.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/874f/3ebe/4715/069c/e2d3/IMG_0268.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/874f/3ebe/4715/069c/e2d3/IMG_0268.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/874f/3ebe/4715/069c/e2d3/IMG_0268.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/874f/3ebe/4715/069c/e2d3/IMG_0268.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">33<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">68) Lady Bird</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>With her directorial debut, the wry wit and emotional potency of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/greta-gerwig/" target="_blank">Greta Gerwig</a>'s previous work came even sharper into focus  telling a beautifully nuanced coming-of-age story about mothers, daughters, and the hometowns you yearn to leave, only for them to be truly appreciated in the rear-view mirror. <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/saoirse-ronan/" target="_blank">Saoirse Ronan</a> is perfectly precocious as the not-always-likeable Christine 'Lady Bird' McPherson, experiencing fractured friendships, first fuckboys, and fateful fumbles in her final year of high school in 2003 Sacramento.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/lady-bird-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Lady Bird</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-33"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Singin' In The Rain" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/87e5/5165/432a/5b3b/7ac2/IMG_0267.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/87e5/5165/432a/5b3b/7ac2/IMG_0267.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/87e5/5165/432a/5b3b/7ac2/IMG_0267.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/87e5/5165/432a/5b3b/7ac2/IMG_0267.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/87e5/5165/432a/5b3b/7ac2/IMG_0267.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/87e5/5165/432a/5b3b/7ac2/IMG_0267.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">34<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">67) Singin' In The Rain</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>A joyous, vibrant Technicolor celebration of the movies, that's such an essential viewing experience there should perhaps be a law that it feature in every DVD and Blu-ray collection. It's no mere Hollywood self-love exercise, though. As star Don Lockwood, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/gene-kelly/" target="_blank">Gene Kelly</a> brings a sense of exasperation at the film industry's diva-indulging daftness, making it a gentle piss-take, too.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/singin-rain-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Singin' In The Rain</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-17"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-34"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="One Flew Over The Cuckoo's Nest" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8874/f590/5eaa/9306/4815/IMG_0266.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8874/f590/5eaa/9306/4815/IMG_0266.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8874/f590/5eaa/9306/4815/IMG_0266.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8874/f590/5eaa/9306/4815/IMG_0266.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8874/f590/5eaa/9306/4815/IMG_0266.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8874/f590/5eaa/9306/4815/IMG_0266.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">35<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">66) One Flew Over The Cuckoo's Nest</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Ken Kesey's era-defining novel was in good hands with screenwriters Lawrence Hauben and Bo Goldman, not to mention director <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/milos-forman/" target="_blank">Milos Forman</a>: five Oscars were testament to that, including one for <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jack-nicholson/" target="_blank">Jack Nicholson</a>, who's arguably never been better as a man destined to be chewed up by the unfeeling system (ditto <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/louise-fletcher/" target="_blank">Louise Fletcher</a>, who represents that system in the form of Nurse Ratched).</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/one-flew-cuckoo-nest-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of One Flew Over The Cuckoo's Nest</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-35"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Seven Samurai" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8ae9/3ebe/473d/239c/e2f5/qvZ91FwMq6O47VViAr8vZNQz3WI.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8ae9/3ebe/473d/239c/e2f5/qvZ91FwMq6O47VViAr8vZNQz3WI.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8ae9/3ebe/473d/239c/e2f5/qvZ91FwMq6O47VViAr8vZNQz3WI.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8ae9/3ebe/473d/239c/e2f5/qvZ91FwMq6O47VViAr8vZNQz3WI.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8ae9/3ebe/473d/239c/e2f5/qvZ91FwMq6O47VViAr8vZNQz3WI.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8ae9/3ebe/473d/239c/e2f5/qvZ91FwMq6O47VViAr8vZNQz3WI.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">36<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">65) Seven Samurai</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>A film so good they remade it twice  as <em>The Magnificent Seven</em>, then as <em>Battle Beyond The Stars</em>. Or four times, arguably... if you count <em>A Bug's Life</em> and the remake of <em>The Magnificent Seven</em>. You could also make the case that <em>Avengers Assemble</em> is a version, too. The point is this: <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/akira-kurosawa/" target="_blank">Akira Kurosawa</a>'s epic, 16th century-set drama about a motley gang of warriors uniting to save a village from bandits couldn't be more influential. Cinema simply wouldn't be the same without it.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/seven-samurai-review/">Read Empire's review of Seven Samurai</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-18"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-36"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="La La Land" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8923/5909/d051/f14c/8788/IMG_0265.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8923/5909/d051/f14c/8788/IMG_0265.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8923/5909/d051/f14c/8788/IMG_0265.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8923/5909/d051/f14c/8788/IMG_0265.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8923/5909/d051/f14c/8788/IMG_0265.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8923/5909/d051/f14c/8788/IMG_0265.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">37<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">64) La La Land</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>As much a technical marvel as it is an acting tour-de-force, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/damien-chazelle/" target="_blank">Damien Chazelle</a>'s Los Angeles love letter proved a ridiculously easy movie to fall in love with, even for those who may have grumbled that they weren't really into musicals before sitting down to watch it. Go on, admit it: You're still humming "Another Day Of Sun", aren't you?</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/la-la-land-review-2/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of La La Land</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-37"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Get Out" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/897b/dbee/af58/a168/ff31/IMG_0264.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/897b/dbee/af58/a168/ff31/IMG_0264.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/897b/dbee/af58/a168/ff31/IMG_0264.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/897b/dbee/af58/a168/ff31/IMG_0264.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/897b/dbee/af58/a168/ff31/IMG_0264.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/897b/dbee/af58/a168/ff31/IMG_0264.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">38<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">63) Get Out</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Even given the darker tones of a few Key And Peele sketches, no one could have predicted that <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jordan-peele/" target="_blank">Jordan Peele</a> would place himself on track to become a modern master of horror. And it all started with this, the Oscar-winning kick-off to his film career in which <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/daniel-kaluuya/" target="_blank">Daniel Kaluuya</a>'s Chris meets his girlfriend Rose's (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/allison-williams/" target="_blank">Allison Williams</a>) parents and discovers some truly shocking secrets. White guilt, specific racism, slavery and more blend into a socially conscious terror tale that rings every note with pitch-perfect accuracy. You'll never look at a cup of tea the same way again.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/get-2-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Get Out</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-19"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-38"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Lawrence Of Arabia" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8bb0/dbee/afde/0568/ff45/IMG_0263.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8bb0/dbee/afde/0568/ff45/IMG_0263.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8bb0/dbee/afde/0568/ff45/IMG_0263.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8bb0/dbee/afde/0568/ff45/IMG_0263.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8bb0/dbee/afde/0568/ff45/IMG_0263.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8bb0/dbee/afde/0568/ff45/IMG_0263.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">39<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">62) Lawrence Of Arabia</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>If you only ever see one <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/david-lean/" target="_blank">David Lean</a> movie... well, don't. Watch as many as you can. But if you really insist on only seeing one <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/peter-otoole/" target="_blank">David Lean</a> movie, then make sure it's <em>Lawrence Of Arabia</em>, the movie that put both the "sweeping" and the "epic" into "sweeping epic" with its breath-taking depiction of T.E. Lawrence's (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/peter-otoole/" target="_blank">Peter O'Toole</a>) Arab-uniting efforts against the German-allied Turks during World War I. It's a different world to the one we're in now, of course, but Lean's mastery of expansive storytelling does much to smooth out any elements (such as <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/alec-guinness/" target="_blank">Alec Guinness</a> playing an Arab) that may rankle modern sensibilities.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/lawrence-arabia-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Lawrence Of Arabia</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-39"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Pan's Labyrinth" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8c75/5909/d024/fc4c/879c/IMG_0262.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8c75/5909/d024/fc4c/879c/IMG_0262.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8c75/5909/d024/fc4c/879c/IMG_0262.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8c75/5909/d024/fc4c/879c/IMG_0262.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8c75/5909/d024/fc4c/879c/IMG_0262.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8c75/5909/d024/fc4c/879c/IMG_0262.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">40<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">61) Pan's Labyrinth</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/guillermo-del-toro/" target="_blank">Guillermo Del Toro</a>'s fairy tale for grown-ups, as pull-no-punches brutal as it is gorgeously, baroquely fantastical. There's an earthy, primal feel to his fairy-world here, alien and threatening rather than gasp-inducing and 'magical', thanks in no small part to the truly cheese-dream nightmarish demon-things Del Toro conjures up, sans CGI, with the assistance of performer <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/doug-jones/" target="_blank">Doug Jones</a>.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/pan-labyrinth-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Pan's Labyrinth</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-20"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-40"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Hot Fuzz" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8cf3/5909/d066/d84c/87a0/IMG_0261.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8cf3/5909/d066/d84c/87a0/IMG_0261.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8cf3/5909/d066/d84c/87a0/IMG_0261.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8cf3/5909/d066/d84c/87a0/IMG_0261.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8cf3/5909/d066/d84c/87a0/IMG_0261.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8cf3/5909/d066/d84c/87a0/IMG_0261.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">41<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">60) Hot Fuzz</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/edgar-wright/" target="_blank">Edgar Wright</a>, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/simon-pegg/" target="_blank">Simon Pegg</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/nick-frost/" target="_blank">Nick Frost</a>'s tribute to big American cop movies isn't just a great fish-out-of-water comedy, sending high-achieving London policeman Nick Angel (Pegg) to the most boring place in the UK (or so it seems). It also manages to wring every last drip of funny out of executing spot-on bombastic, Bayhem-style action in a sleepy English small-town setting.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/hot-fuzz-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Hot Fuzz</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-41"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Moonlight" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8dc6/5909/d069/db4c/87a7/IMG_0259.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8dc6/5909/d069/db4c/87a7/IMG_0259.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8dc6/5909/d069/db4c/87a7/IMG_0259.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8dc6/5909/d069/db4c/87a7/IMG_0259.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8dc6/5909/d069/db4c/87a7/IMG_0259.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8dc6/5909/d069/db4c/87a7/IMG_0259.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">42<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">59) Moonlight</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Adapted from Tarell Alvin's play <em>In Moonlight, Black Boys Look Blue</em>, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/barry-jenkins/" target="_blank">Barry Jenkins</a>' Oscar-winning drama is the kind of film that seeps under your skin and stays there. Tracking one man's life in three stages, and the love (and lack of it) that made him who he is, <em>Moonlight</em> evokes a sense of intimacy so palpable, the camera's gaze into the characters' eyes so intense, you can't bear to look away. <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/naomie-harris/" target="_blank">Mahershala Ali</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/naomie-harris/" target="_blank">Naomie Harris</a> are impeccable in supporting roles, with <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/trevante-rhodes/" target="_blank">Trevante Rhodes</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/andre-holland/" target="_blank">Andre Holland</a> delivering an unforgettable final act.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/moonlight-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Moonlight.</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-21"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-42"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Guardians Of The Galaxy" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8ec4/f590/5e32/6e06/4844/IMG_0258.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8ec4/f590/5e32/6e06/4844/IMG_0258.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8ec4/f590/5e32/6e06/4844/IMG_0258.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8ec4/f590/5e32/6e06/4844/IMG_0258.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8ec4/f590/5e32/6e06/4844/IMG_0258.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8ec4/f590/5e32/6e06/4844/IMG_0258.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">43<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">58) Guardians Of The Galaxy</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Marvel took one of its biggest swings with this space-borne adventure, which featured the MCU's freakiest and least-known characters (a talking raccoon, a walking tree, a green assassin lady, a muscleman named after a Bond villain and Star-who!?), starred that schlubby fellah from <em>Parks And Rec</em>, and was directed by the guy who turned <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/michael-rooker/" target="_blank">Michael Rooker</a> into a giant slug-monster in <em>Slither</em>. Which is pretty cool, when you think about it.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/guardians-galaxy-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Guardians Of The Galaxy</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-43"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Blade Runner 2049" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8f87/5165/4308/8e3b/7afa/57%20Blade%20Runner%202049.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8f87/5165/4308/8e3b/7afa/57%20Blade%20Runner%202049.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8f87/5165/4308/8e3b/7afa/57%20Blade%20Runner%202049.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8f87/5165/4308/8e3b/7afa/57%20Blade%20Runner%202049.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8f87/5165/4308/8e3b/7afa/57%20Blade%20Runner%202049.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/8f87/5165/4308/8e3b/7afa/57%20Blade%20Runner%202049.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">44<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">57) Blade Runner 2049</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Putting together the director of <em>Arrival</em> with a sci-fi franchise that  for box office performance reasons  hasn't been overexploited the way some others have, seemed like a no-brainer. It's actually a big brainer, with <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/denis-villeneuve/" target="_blank">Denis Villeneuve</a> dipping into <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/philip-k-dick/" target="_blank">Philip K. Dick'</a>s universe and constructing a sequel that not only doesn't embarrass <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/ridley-scott/" target="_blank">Ridley Scott</a>'s original, but builds out that world, adding layers and texture while still feeling of a piece. Audiences still didn't exactly bite, but between <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/harrison-ford/" target="_blank">Harrison Ford</a> revisiting his iconic replicant hunter and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/ryan-gosling/" target="_blank">Ryan Gosling</a> grappling with his own identity, <em>2049</em> is a triumph of quiet character moments and glorious, sense-enveloping spectacle.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/blade-runner-2049-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Blade Runner 2049</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-22"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-44"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Social Network" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/90b2/5165/438b/fe3b/7b01/56%20the%20social%20network.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/90b2/5165/438b/fe3b/7b01/56%20the%20social%20network.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/90b2/5165/438b/fe3b/7b01/56%20the%20social%20network.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/90b2/5165/438b/fe3b/7b01/56%20the%20social%20network.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/90b2/5165/438b/fe3b/7b01/56%20the%20social%20network.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/90b2/5165/438b/fe3b/7b01/56%20the%20social%20network.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">45<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">56) The Social Network</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Or, I'm Gonna Git You Zuckerberg. Portrayed as an ber-ruthless ultra-nerd by <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jesse-eisenberg/" target="_blank">Jesse Eisenberg</a>, it's fair to say the Facebook founder came out of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/david-fincher/" target="_blank">David Fincher</a>'s social-media drama smelling less of roses than the stuff you grow them in. But it is great drama, expertly wrought by screenwriter <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/aaron-sorkin/" target="_blank">Aaron Sorkin</a>, who exploits the story's central paradox (a guy who doesn't get people makes a fortune getting people together online) to supremely juicy effect.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/social-network-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Social Network</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-45"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Taxi Driver" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/911c/5909/d06a/1a4c/87c6/55%20Taxi%20Driver.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/911c/5909/d06a/1a4c/87c6/55%20Taxi%20Driver.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/911c/5909/d06a/1a4c/87c6/55%20Taxi%20Driver.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/911c/5909/d06a/1a4c/87c6/55%20Taxi%20Driver.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/911c/5909/d06a/1a4c/87c6/55%20Taxi%20Driver.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/911c/5909/d06a/1a4c/87c6/55%20Taxi%20Driver.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">46<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">55) Taxi Driver</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/martin-scorsese/" target="_blank">Martin Scorsese</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/paul-schrader/" target="_blank">Paul Schrader</a>'s gripping portrayal of a mentally crumbling Vietnam vet (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/robert-de-niro/" target="_blank">Robert De Niro</a>'s Travis Bickle) who ultimately figures the only way to wash the crime-caked streets of New York is with a nice, big bloodbath. Everyone here's at the top of their game: Scorsese, Schrader, De Niro, 14-year-old <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jodie-foster/" target="_blank">Jodie Foster</a> and composer <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/bernard-herrmann/" target="_blank">Bernard Herrmann</a>. Yes, it's still talkin' to us.</p>

class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">47<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">54) Saving Private Ryan</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>The sheer bludgeoning, blood-spilling, visceral power of its Omaha Beach, D-Day-landing opening act ensured that <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/steven-spielberg/" target="_blank">Steven Spielberg</a>'s fourth World War II movie set the standard for all future battle depictions. Its shaky-staccato-desaturated style (courtesy of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/janusz-kaminski/" target="_blank">Janusz Kaminski</a>'s ingenious cinematography) newsreel made cinema has been oft-copied, but rarely bettered.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/saving-private-ryan-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Saving Private Ryan</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-47"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Forrest Gump" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9291/5165/4384/c73b/7b1b/53%20Forrest%20Gump.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9291/5165/4384/c73b/7b1b/53%20Forrest%20Gump.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9291/5165/4384/c73b/7b1b/53%20Forrest%20Gump.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9291/5165/4384/c73b/7b1b/53%20Forrest%20Gump.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9291/5165/4384/c73b/7b1b/53%20Forrest%20Gump.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9291/5165/4384/c73b/7b1b/53%20Forrest%20Gump.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">48<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">53) Forrest Gump</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/robert-zemeckis/" target="_blank">Robert Zemeckis</a>' affable stroll through some of America's most turbulent decades, as seen through the childlike eyes of the simple-but-successful Forrest  the role which earned <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/tom-hanks/" target="_blank">Tom Hanks</a> his second Oscar in two years. And it says a lot about the film's emotional heft that it managed to win an Oscar itself, when it was in competition with both <em>Pulp Fiction</em> and <em>The Shawshank Redemption</em>.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/forrest-gump-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Forrest Gump</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-24"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-48"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Point Break" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9334/f590/5e93/9206/4860/52%20Point%20Break.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9334/f590/5e93/9206/4860/52%20Point%20Break.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9334/f590/5e93/9206/4860/52%20Point%20Break.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9334/f590/5e93/9206/4860/52%20Point%20Break.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9334/f590/5e93/9206/4860/52%20Point%20Break.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9334/f590/5e93/9206/4860/52%20Point%20Break.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">49<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">52)  Point Break</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>"Ever fired your gun in the air and gone 'Ahhhh?'" PC Danny Butterman's well-placed reference in <em>Hot Fuzz</em> confirmed, if confirmation were ever needed, that <em>Point Break</em> is a fundamental pillar of '90s pop culture cool, and one of the most memorable action blockbusters ever made. In <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/keanu-reeves/" target="_blank">Keanu Reeves</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/patrick-swayze/" target="_blank">Patrick Swayze</a>, we get two smouldering sides of the same anti-heroic coin; in W. Peter Iliff's screenplay, we get gems of dialogue like "The correct term is 'babes', sir"; and in <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/kathryn-bigelow/" target="_blank">Kathryn Bigelow</a>'s frenetic, confident direction, we get intense foot chases, fiery shoot-outs, epic surfing, and a spot of light skydiving. It shouldn't work: extreme sports, bank robberies <em>and</em> male bonding? But it does, every time.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/point-break-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Point Break</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-49"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Whiplash" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/93fa/f590/5e39/9506/4868/51%20Whiplash.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/93fa/f590/5e39/9506/4868/51%20Whiplash.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/93fa/f590/5e39/9506/4868/51%20Whiplash.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/93fa/f590/5e39/9506/4868/51%20Whiplash.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/93fa/f590/5e39/9506/4868/51%20Whiplash.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/93fa/f590/5e39/9506/4868/51%20Whiplash.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">50<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">51) Whiplash</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>If <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/damien-chazelle/" target="_blank">Damien Chazelle</a>'s semi-autobiographical drama taught us anything, it's that jazz drumming is more hazardous to learn than base jumping. Especially when your mentor is <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jk-simmons/" target="_blank">J.K. Simmons</a>' monstrous Fletcher: a raging bully who makes army drill instructors look like Care Bears. Though, of course, you could always argue that Fletcher's methods certainly got great results out of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/miles-teller/" target="_blank">Miles Teller</a>'s battered but triumphant Andrew...</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/whiplash-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Whiplash</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-25"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-50"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Vertigo" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9502/f590/5e19/4d06/4874/50%20VERTIGO.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9502/f590/5e19/4d06/4874/50%20VERTIGO.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9502/f590/5e19/4d06/4874/50%20VERTIGO.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9502/f590/5e19/4d06/4874/50%20VERTIGO.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9502/f590/5e19/4d06/4874/50%20VERTIGO.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9502/f590/5e19/4d06/4874/50%20VERTIGO.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">51<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">50) Vertigo</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>If <em>Psycho</em> was <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/alfred-hitchcock/" target="_blank">Hitchcock</a>'s big shocker, then <em>Vertigo</em> is the one that gets properly under your skin. With <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/james-stewart/" target="_blank">James Stewart</a>'s detective stalking Kim Novak's mysterious woman, witnessing her suicide, then becoming obsessed with her double, it's certainly disturbing and most definitely (as the title suggests) disorientating. In the most artful and inventive way.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/vertigo-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Vertigo</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-51"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Spirited Away" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/96cd/3ebe/47b1/8d9c/e366/49%20Spririted%20Away.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/96cd/3ebe/47b1/8d9c/e366/49%20Spririted%20Away.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/96cd/3ebe/47b1/8d9c/e366/49%20Spririted%20Away.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/96cd/3ebe/47b1/8d9c/e366/49%20Spririted%20Away.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/96cd/3ebe/47b1/8d9c/e366/49%20Spririted%20Away.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/96cd/3ebe/47b1/8d9c/e366/49%20Spririted%20Away.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">52<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">49) Spirited Away</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>For a Western world raised on Disney movies, <em>Spirited Away</em> was a bracing change of pace  pure, uncut Studio Ghibli. Taking in bathhouses, spirits of Shinto folklore, and morality without clear-cut distinctions of good and evil, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/hayao-miyazaki/" target="_blank">Hayao Miyazaki</a>'s major crossover hit is distinctly Japanese. It's the film that brought Studio Ghibli  and anime at large  to mainstream Western audiences, an influence increasingly felt in the likes of <em>Moana</em> and <em>Frozen II</em>.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/spirited-away-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Spirited Away</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-26"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-52"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Ghostbusters" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9760/f590/5ec3/4206/488d/48%20Ghostbusters.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9760/f590/5ec3/4206/488d/48%20Ghostbusters.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9760/f590/5ec3/4206/488d/48%20Ghostbusters.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9760/f590/5ec3/4206/488d/48%20Ghostbusters.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9760/f590/5ec3/4206/488d/48%20Ghostbusters.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9760/f590/5ec3/4206/488d/48%20Ghostbusters.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">53<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">48) Ghostbusters</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>As high-concept comedies go, <em>Ghostbusters</em> is positively stratospheric: a story of demonic incursion... with gags! And it manages to wring a fantastic supernatural adventure out of that concept, while never neglecting the opportunity to deliver a great laugh; or, on the flipside, ever allowing the zaniness to swallow up plot coherence. Ray Parker Jr was right. Bustin' did indeed make us feel good.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/ghostbusters-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Ghostbusters</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-53"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Do The Right Thing" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/97c2/f590/5e65/9506/4892/47%20Do%20The%20Right%20THing.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/97c2/f590/5e65/9506/4892/47%20Do%20The%20Right%20THing.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/97c2/f590/5e65/9506/4892/47%20Do%20The%20Right%20THing.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/97c2/f590/5e65/9506/4892/47%20Do%20The%20Right%20THing.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/97c2/f590/5e65/9506/4892/47%20Do%20The%20Right%20THing.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/97c2/f590/5e65/9506/4892/47%20Do%20The%20Right%20THing.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">54<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">47) Do The Right Thing</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/spike-lee/" target="_blank">Spike Lee</a> had already caused a stir with his first two films  <em>She's Gotta Have It</em> and <em>School Daze</em>  but this was the one that changed everything, with Lee at full pelt, fully formed, in full command and full of fury. Over the longest, hottest summer's day in Brooklyn's Bed-Stuy, already boiling tensions between the African-Americans on the block and the Italian-Americans running a pizzeria eventually peak, erupting into violence. It's an absolutely flawless, funny, frightening piece of work, rammed with soon-to-be iconography from start to finish. It hasn't dated a day.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/right-thing-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Do The Right Thing</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-27"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-54"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Schindler's List" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9866/f590/5e19/e406/4898/46%20schindler's%20list.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9866/f590/5e19/e406/4898/46%20schindler's%20list.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9866/f590/5e19/e406/4898/46%20schindler's%20list.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9866/f590/5e19/e406/4898/46%20schindler's%20list.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9866/f590/5e19/e406/4898/46%20schindler's%20list.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9866/f590/5e19/e406/4898/46%20schindler's%20list.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">55<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">46) Schindler's List</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Spielberg's masterpiece, hands down. You might say the shark looks fakey in Jaws. You may wonder how Indy clung to the German sub in Raiders. But there's no flaws to be found in his harrowing, (mostly) monochromatic depiction of Nazi persecution of the Jewish community in Krakow. Unless you're the kind of shallow person who only watches movies that are 'entertaining'. In which case, you're missing out.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/schindler-list-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Schindler's List</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-55"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Big Lebowaki" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/98da/dbee/af5c/b168/ffb2/45%20~the%20Big%20Lebowski.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/98da/dbee/af5c/b168/ffb2/45%20~the%20Big%20Lebowski.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/98da/dbee/af5c/b168/ffb2/45%20~the%20Big%20Lebowski.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/98da/dbee/af5c/b168/ffb2/45%20~the%20Big%20Lebowski.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/98da/dbee/af5c/b168/ffb2/45%20~the%20Big%20Lebowski.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/98da/dbee/af5c/b168/ffb2/45%20~the%20Big%20Lebowski.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">56<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">45) The Big Lebowski</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>You've got to hand it to the Coen brothers. Not only did they make arguably the funniest movie of the '90s  which has since spawned a genuine film cult  they also managed to construct a kidnap mystery in which the detective isn't a detective and nobody was actually kidnapped. With bowling, marmots and a urine-stained rug.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/big-lebowski-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Big Lebowski</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-28"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-56"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="It's A Wonderful" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw"
