width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">57<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">44) It's A Wonderful Life</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Frank Capra's Christmas fantasy was the movie that coaxed a war-battered <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/james-stewart/" target="_blank">James Stewart</a> back to acting, and a good thing, too: as George Bailey, who's shown a mind-blowing parallel reality in which he never existed, Stewart was never more appealing. And he tempers any potential schmaltz, too, with a sense of underlying world-weariness  one that he no doubt brought back from the conflict in Europe.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/wonderful-life-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of It's A Wonderful Life</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-57"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="There Will Be Blood" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9a3d/dbee/afd9/ba68/ffbf/43%20There%20Will%20Be%20Blood.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9a3d/dbee/afd9/ba68/ffbf/43%20There%20Will%20Be%20Blood.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9a3d/dbee/afd9/ba68/ffbf/43%20There%20Will%20Be%20Blood.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9a3d/dbee/afd9/ba68/ffbf/43%20There%20Will%20Be%20Blood.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9a3d/dbee/afd9/ba68/ffbf/43%20There%20Will%20Be%20Blood.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9a3d/dbee/afd9/ba68/ffbf/43%20There%20Will%20Be%20Blood.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">58<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">43) There Will Be Blood</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>If America were a person, then oil man Daniel Plainview (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/daniel-day-lewis/" target="_blank">Daniel Day-Lewis</a>) is a vampire. (A milkshake-drinking vampire, if you feel like mixing our metaphor with his own.) Which is why it's appropriate that <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/paul-thomas-anderson/" target="_blank">Paul Thomas Anderson</a> gives the film a bit of a horror-movie vibe throughout and Day-Lewis delivers such a deliciously monstrous performance... right up to the point where he spills literal blood in an empty mansion, haunted only by himself.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/will-blood-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of There Will Be Blood</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-29"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-58"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="12 Angry Men" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9aee/dbee/af39/3368/ffcb/42%2012%20Angry%20Men.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9aee/dbee/af39/3368/ffcb/42%2012%20Angry%20Men.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9aee/dbee/af39/3368/ffcb/42%2012%20Angry%20Men.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9aee/dbee/af39/3368/ffcb/42%2012%20Angry%20Men.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9aee/dbee/af39/3368/ffcb/42%2012%20Angry%20Men.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9aee/dbee/af39/3368/ffcb/42%2012%20Angry%20Men.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">59<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">42) 12 Angry Men</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Juries most often amount to little more than set dressing in courtroom dramas. But <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/sidney-lumet/" target="_blank">Sidney Lumet</a>'s film finds all its drama outside the courtroom itself and inside a jury deliberation room packed with fantastic character actors, who are forced to re-examine a seemingly straightforward case by lone-voice juror Henry Fonda. It's all about the value of looking at things differently, and a reminder that nothing is more important than great dialogue.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/twelve-angry-men-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of 12 Angry Men</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-59"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Silence Of The Lambs" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9b60/5909/d020/b74c/8816/41%20Silence%20of%20the%20lambs.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9b60/5909/d020/b74c/8816/41%20Silence%20of%20the%20lambs.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9b60/5909/d020/b74c/8816/41%20Silence%20of%20the%20lambs.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9b60/5909/d020/b74c/8816/41%20Silence%20of%20the%20lambs.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9b60/5909/d020/b74c/8816/41%20Silence%20of%20the%20lambs.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9b60/5909/d020/b74c/8816/41%20Silence%20of%20the%20lambs.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">60<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">41) The Silence Of The Lambs</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Not only the first horror to win a Best Picture Oscar, it's also only the third movie to score in all four main categories: Picture, Director (the late, great <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jonathan-demme/" target="_blank">Jonathan Demme</a>), Actress (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jodie-foster/" target="_blank">Jodie Foster</a>) and Actor (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/anthony-hopkins/" target="_blank">Anthony Hopkins</a>)  the latter managing that despite technically being a supporting performer, with a mere 25-ish minutes of screen time. Even so, it feels like Foster's movie more than anybody's: her vulnerable-but-steely Clarice Starling is defined by her ability, not her gender.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/silence-lambs-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Silence Of The Lambs</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-30"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-60"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Citizen Kane" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9c19/5165/4386/2f3b/7b61/40%20Citizen%20kane.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9c19/5165/4386/2f3b/7b61/40%20Citizen%20kane.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9c19/5165/4386/2f3b/7b61/40%20Citizen%20kane.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9c19/5165/4386/2f3b/7b61/40%20Citizen%20kane.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9c19/5165/4386/2f3b/7b61/40%20Citizen%20kane.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/9c19/5165/4386/2f3b/7b61/40%20Citizen%20kane.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">61<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">40)  Citizen Kane</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/orson-welles/" target="_blank">Orson Welles</a>' game-changing fictional biopic, that managed to both launch his film career and ruin it at the same time (turns out it's not a good idea to piss off powerful newspaper magnates by viciously satirising them to a mass audience). Not only did he use impressive new film-making techniques that make it feel like a movie far younger than its 76 years, but its power-corrupts story still resonates loudly. Now more than ever, in fact.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/citizen-kane-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Citizen Kane</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-61"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Gladiator" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a127/dbee/af31/5c68/ffff/39%20Gladiator.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a127/dbee/af31/5c68/ffff/39%20Gladiator.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a127/dbee/af31/5c68/ffff/39%20Gladiator.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a127/dbee/af31/5c68/ffff/39%20Gladiator.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a127/dbee/af31/5c68/ffff/39%20Gladiator.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a127/dbee/af31/5c68/ffff/39%20Gladiator.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">62<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">39) Gladiator</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/ridley-scott/" target="_blank">Ridley Scott</a>'s comeback (after a bad run with 1492, White Squall and G.I. Jane). <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/russell-crowe/" target="_blank">Russell Crowe'</a>s big Hollywood breakthrough. And, thanks to the scope of Scott's visual ambition combined with a leap forward in CGI quality, the movie that showed the industry you could make colossal historical epics commercially viable once more. Yes, we were entertained.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/gladiator-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Gladiator</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-31"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">63<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">38) The Good, The Bad And The Ugly</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Sergio Leone sets three renegades against each other in a treasure hunt backdropped against the chaos and madness of the American Civil War. The result is the movie on his CV which best balances art and entertainment. <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/clint-eastwood/" target="_blank">Clint Eastwood</a> and Lee Van Cleef are great value as Blondie and Angel Eyes, but it's Eli Wallach's Tuco who steals this Wild West show: "When you have to shoot, shoot. Don't talk."</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/good-bad-ugly-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Good, The Bad And The Ugly</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-63"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Se7en" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a2b0/f590/5e90/2c06/48e9/37%20Se7en.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a2b0/f590/5e90/2c06/48e9/37%20Se7en.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a2b0/f590/5e90/2c06/48e9/37%20Se7en.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a2b0/f590/5e90/2c06/48e9/37%20Se7en.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a2b0/f590/5e90/2c06/48e9/37%20Se7en.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a2b0/f590/5e90/2c06/48e9/37%20Se7en.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">64<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">37) Se7en</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Aka <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/david-fincher/" target="_blank">David Fincher</a>'s second debut movie. What sounded like a daft, novelty serial-killer thriller turned out to be a deeply rattling proper-shocker, which had the guts to throw down its biggest narrative twist halfway through, as warped murderer-moralist John Doe gives himself up. A twist made all the more effective thanks to <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/kevin-spacey/" target="_blank">Kevin Spacey</a>'s insistence he wasn't billed until the end credits.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/seven-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Seven</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-32"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">65<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">36) Eternal Sunshine Of The Spotless Mind</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Director <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/michel-gondry/" target="_blank">Michel Gondry</a> and screenwriter <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/charlie-kaufman/" target="_blank">Charlie Kaufman</a> deconstruct the relationship drama via a fantastic psycho-sci-fi device, as <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jim-carrey/" target="_blank">Jim Carrey</a>'s Joel races through his own mind to reverse a process by which all his memories of his failed relationship with <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/kate-winslet/" target="_blank">Kate Winslet</a>'s Clementine are to be erased. Which is a brilliantly weird, round-the-houses way of reminding us that heartbreak should be valued as one of the things that makes us. Better to have loved and lost, and all that.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/eternal-sunshine-spotless-mind-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Eternal Sunshine Of The Spotless Mind</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-65"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Shining" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a62c/f590/5e4e/8606/4906/35%20shining.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a62c/f590/5e4e/8606/4906/35%20shining.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a62c/f590/5e4e/8606/4906/35%20shining.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a62c/f590/5e4e/8606/4906/35%20shining.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a62c/f590/5e4e/8606/4906/35%20shining.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/a62c/f590/5e4e/8606/4906/35%20shining.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">66<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">35) The Shining</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/stanley-kubrick/" target="_blank">Stanley Kubrick</a>'s elegant adaptation of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/stephen-king/" target="_blank">Stephen King</a>'s haunted-hotel story, starring a wonderfully deranged <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jack-nicholson/" target="_blank">Jack Nicholso</a>n, is often cited as The Scariest Horror Movie Ever Made (perhaps tied with <em>The Exorcist</em>), but it's also the Least Suitable Movie To Watch On Father's Day Ever. Unless you're the kind of Dad who thinks obsessively typing the same sentence over and over then chasing after your wife and kid with an axe constitutes good parenting.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/shining-2-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Shining</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-33"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-66"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Lord Of The Rings: The Two Towers" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ac02/dbee/af63/3369/005b/34%20two%20towers.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ac02/dbee/af63/3369/005b/34%20two%20towers.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ac02/dbee/af63/3369/005b/34%20two%20towers.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ac02/dbee/af63/3369/005b/34%20two%20towers.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ac02/dbee/af63/3369/005b/34%20two%20towers.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ac02/dbee/af63/3369/005b/34%20two%20towers.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">67<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">34) The Lord Of The Rings: The Two Towers</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Aside from Boromir, Aragorn and the small-town denizens of Bree, there's not a huge amount of human representation in <em>The Fellowship Of The Ring</em>. So one of the pleasures of <em>The Two Towers</em> is seeing Middle-earth truly open out after the arrival at Rohan, where the series takes on more of a sweeping, Nordic feel... Building up, of course, to Helm's Deep, a ferocious action crescendo which features gratuitous scenes of dwarf-tossing.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/lord-rings-two-towers-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Two Towers</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-67"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Casablanca" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ac59/5165/434b/4c3b/7bdf/33%20Casablanca.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ac59/5165/434b/4c3b/7bdf/33%20Casablanca.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ac59/5165/434b/4c3b/7bdf/33%20Casablanca.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ac59/5165/434b/4c3b/7bdf/33%20Casablanca.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ac59/5165/434b/4c3b/7bdf/33%20Casablanca.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ac59/5165/434b/4c3b/7bdf/33%20Casablanca.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">68<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">33) Casablanca</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>When you've got such a clear-cut good-vs-evil scenario as World War II, it takes guts to put out a film which lets its (anti-) hero lurk for so long in a grey area of that conflict  while said War was still raging, no less. Of course, Rick (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/humphrey-bogart/" target="_blank">Humphrey Bogart</a>) eventually does the right thing, but watching him make both the Resistance and the Nazis squirm right up to the final scene is truly joyous.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/casablanca-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Casablanca</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-34"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-68"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Thing" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ad03/5909/d018/5b4c/889e/32%20The%20Thing.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ad03/5909/d018/5b4c/889e/32%20The%20Thing.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ad03/5909/d018/5b4c/889e/32%20The%20Thing.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ad03/5909/d018/5b4c/889e/32%20The%20Thing.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ad03/5909/d018/5b4c/889e/32%20The%20Thing.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ad03/5909/d018/5b4c/889e/32%20The%20Thing.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">69<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">32) The Thing</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Any argument about whether or not modern remakes can ever be better than the 'classic' originals should be ended pretty quickly by mentioning this movie. With the help of SFX genius <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/rob-bottin/" target="_blank">Rob Bottin</a>, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/john-carpenter/" target="_blank">John Carpenter</a> took the bones of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/howard-hawks/" target="_blank">Howard Hawks</a>' 1951 <em>The Thing From Another World</em> and crafted an intense, frosty sci-fi thriller featuring Hollywood's ultimate movie monster: one that could be any of us at any time, before contorting into a genuine biological nightmare.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/thing-2-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Thing</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-69"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Interstellar" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/adf6/5165/4363/823b/7bf0/31%20Interstellar.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/adf6/5165/4363/823b/7bf0/31%20Interstellar.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/adf6/5165/4363/823b/7bf0/31%20Interstellar.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/adf6/5165/4363/823b/7bf0/31%20Interstellar.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/adf6/5165/4363/823b/7bf0/31%20Interstellar.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/adf6/5165/4363/823b/7bf0/31%20Interstellar.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">70<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">31) Interstellar</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/christopher-nolan/" target="_blank">Christopher Nolan</a>'s tribute to <em>2001</em> and <em>The Right Stuff</em> (with a little added <em>The Black Hole</em>) presents long-distance space travel as realistically as it's possible to with the theoretical physics currently available. From the effects of gravity to the emotional implication of time dilation, it mixes science and sentiment to great effect. And it has a sarcastic robot, too.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/interstellar-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Interstellar</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-35"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-70"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Heat" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ae64/5909/d067/8f4c/88aa/30%20Heat.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ae64/5909/d067/8f4c/88aa/30%20Heat.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ae64/5909/d067/8f4c/88aa/30%20Heat.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ae64/5909/d067/8f4c/88aa/30%20Heat.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ae64/5909/d067/8f4c/88aa/30%20Heat.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ae64/5909/d067/8f4c/88aa/30%20Heat.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">71<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">30) Heat</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/michael-mann/" target="_blank">Michael Mann</a>'s starry upgrade of his TV movie <em>LA Takedown</em> squeezed every last drop of icon-juice out of its heavyweight double-billing, bringing <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/al-pacino/" target="_blank">Pacino</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/robert-de-niro/" target="_blank">De Niro</a> together on screen, sharing scenes for the very first time. The trick was to only do it twice during the entire running time, with that first diner meeting virtually fizzing with alpha-star electricity.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/heat-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Heat</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-71"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Apocalypse Now" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/aefa/f590/5ecf/da06/493e/29%20Apocalypse%20Now.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/aefa/f590/5ecf/da06/493e/29%20Apocalypse%20Now.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/aefa/f590/5ecf/da06/493e/29%20Apocalypse%20Now.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/aefa/f590/5ecf/da06/493e/29%20Apocalypse%20Now.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/aefa/f590/5ecf/da06/493e/29%20Apocalypse%20Now.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/aefa/f590/5ecf/da06/493e/29%20Apocalypse%20Now.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">72<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">29) Apocalypse Now</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>The film-maker go-to movie du jour. <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/gareth-edwards/" target="_blank">Gareth Edwards</a> cited <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/francis-ford-coppola/" target="_blank">Coppola</a>'s vivid and visceral jungle trek as a major influence on <em>Rogue One</em>; <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/jordan-vogt-roberts/" target="_blank">Jordan Vogt-Roberts</a> drew from it extensively for <em>Kong: Skull Island</em>, and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/matt-reeves/" target="_blank">Matt Reeves</a> sees <em>War For The Planet Of The Apes</em> as his own simian-related tribute. Hardly surprising; it's both a visually rich war movie and also a powerfully resonant journey into the darkest recesses of the human soul.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/apocalypse-now-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Apocalypse Now</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-36"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-72"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Indiana Jones And The Last Crusade" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/afcb/5909/d038/5d4c/88b3/28%20Last%20Crusade.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/afcb/5909/d038/5d4c/88b3/28%20Last%20Crusade.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/afcb/5909/d038/5d4c/88b3/28%20Last%20Crusade.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/afcb/5909/d038/5d4c/88b3/28%20Last%20Crusade.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/afcb/5909/d038/5d4c/88b3/28%20Last%20Crusade.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/afcb/5909/d038/5d4c/88b3/28%20Last%20Crusade.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">73<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">28) Indiana Jones And The Last Crusade</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>You voted... wisely. There may only be 12 years' difference between <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/harrison-ford/" target="_blank">Harrison Ford</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/sean-connery/" target="_blank">Sean Connery</a>, but it's hard to imagine two better actors to play a bickering father and son, off on a globetrotting, Nazi-bashing, mythical mystery tour. After all, you've got <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/steven-spielberg/" target="_blank">Spielberg</a>/<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/george-lucas/" target="_blank">Lucas</a>' own version of James Bond... And the original Bond himself.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/indiana-jones-last-crusade-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Indiana Jones And The Last Crusade</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-73"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Lord Of The Rings The Return Of The King" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b0b1/f590/5e55/dc06/4949/27%20Return%20of%20the%20king.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b0b1/f590/5e55/dc06/4949/27%20Return%20of%20the%20king.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b0b1/f590/5e55/dc06/4949/27%20Return%20of%20the%20king.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b0b1/f590/5e55/dc06/4949/27%20Return%20of%20the%20king.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b0b1/f590/5e55/dc06/4949/27%20Return%20of%20the%20king.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b0b1/f590/5e55/dc06/4949/27%20Return%20of%20the%20king.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">74<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">27) The Lord Of The Rings The Return Of The King</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Anyone who bangs on about all those endings is missing the many joys of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/peter-jackson/" target="_blank">Peter Jackson</a>'s Academy Award-laden trilogy-closer. It has some of the most colossal and entertaining battle scenes ever mounted; it has an awesome giant spider; it has that fantastic dramatic-ironic twist when Gollum saves the day through his own treachery; and it has that bit where Eowyn says, "I am no man". Deserves. Every. Oscar.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/lord-rings-return-king-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Return Of The King</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-37"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-74"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Die Hard" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b12e/5165/43e6/133b/7c10/26%20Die%20hard.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b12e/5165/43e6/133b/7c10/26%20Die%20hard.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b12e/5165/43e6/133b/7c10/26%20Die%20hard.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b12e/5165/43e6/133b/7c10/26%20Die%20hard.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b12e/5165/43e6/133b/7c10/26%20Die%20hard.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b12e/5165/43e6/133b/7c10/26%20Die%20hard.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">75<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">26) Die Hard</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>One man using only his wits and whatever he can extract from his environment. A gang of bad guys terrorising the locals. If Die Hard wasn't set in a skyscraper during the 1980s, it could easily be a Western. A Western which, in the form of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/bruce-willis/" target="_blank">Bruce Willis</a>, not only convinced the world a TV-comedy star could be an action-hero, but also gave us one of our most seethingly charismatic big-screen villain-players: <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/alan-rickman/" target="_blank">Alan Rickman</a>.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/die-hard-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Die Hard</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-75"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Fight Club" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b191/5909/d009/314c/88c0/25%20Fight%20Club.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b191/5909/d009/314c/88c0/25%20Fight%20Club.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b191/5909/d009/314c/88c0/25%20Fight%20Club.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b191/5909/d009/314c/88c0/25%20Fight%20Club.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b191/5909/d009/314c/88c0/25%20Fight%20Club.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b191/5909/d009/314c/88c0/25%20Fight%20Club.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">76<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">25) Fight Club</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>After all the pre-release hype about how dark and brutal <em>Fight Club</em> was, one of the most surprising things to discover on seeing it was just how funny it actually was. And just as well; if you weren't laughing at Bob's "bitch-tits" or Tyler Durden's human-fat soap-making antics, it would be pretty hard to process <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/david-fincher/" target="_blank">David Fincher</a>'s bravura take on <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/chuck-palahniuk/" target="_blank">Chuck Palahniuk</a>'s tale of modern masculinity running insanely rampant.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/fight-club-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Fight Club</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-38"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-76"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Terminator 2 Judgment Day" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b23f/5165/4381/e83b/7c20/24%20T2.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b23f/5165/4381/e83b/7c20/24%20T2.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b23f/5165/4381/e83b/7c20/24%20T2.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b23f/5165/4381/e83b/7c20/24%20T2.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b23f/5165/4381/e83b/7c20/24%20T2.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b23f/5165/4381/e83b/7c20/24%20T2.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">77<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">24) Terminator 2 Judgment Day</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Making <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/arnold-schwarzenegger/" target="_blank">Arnie'</a>s T-800 a protector rather than killer for part two could have been a shark-jump moment for the <em>Terminator</em> series, but we're talking about <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/james-cameron/" target="_blank">James Cameron</a> here. So it paid off  especially as this Terminator was just as much a student in human behaviour (with John Connor his teacher) as guardian, with some darkly comical results ("He'll live"). Is it really better than the original? In terms of scale and sheer, balls-out action spectacle, yes.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/terminator-2-judgment-day-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Terminator 2: Judgment Day</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-77"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="2001: A Space Odyssey" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b2ce/f590/5e90/7e06/495f/23%202001.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b2ce/f590/5e90/7e06/495f/23%202001.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b2ce/f590/5e90/7e06/495f/23%202001.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b2ce/f590/5e90/7e06/495f/23%202001.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b2ce/f590/5e90/7e06/495f/23%202001.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b2ce/f590/5e90/7e06/495f/23%202001.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">78<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">23) 2001: A Space Odyssey</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>You've voted it your favourite <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/stanley-kubrick/" target="_blank">Kubrick</a> movie, which makes sense to us. It is arguably his greatest gift to cinema, an infinitely ambitious vision of a space-faring future whose narrative centres on the most pivotal moment in human evolution since some ape-man first bashed another ape-man with an old bone. Graceful, gorgeous, unwearied by time's passing. Rather like that monolith.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/2001-space-odyssey-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of 2001: A Space Odyssey</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-39"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-78"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Avengers: Endgame" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b34d/f590/5eee/8e06/4963/22%20Endgame.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b34d/f590/5eee/8e06/4963/22%20Endgame.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b34d/f590/5eee/8e06/4963/22%20Endgame.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b34d/f590/5eee/8e06/4963/22%20Endgame.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b34d/f590/5eee/8e06/4963/22%20Endgame.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b34d/f590/5eee/8e06/4963/22%20Endgame.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">79<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">22) Avengers: Endgame</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>What does it take to dethrone <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/james-cameron/" target="_blank">James Cameron</a>? A blockbuster of behemothic proportions. The weight of expectations on <em>Endgame</em>  the culmination of 11 years of interweaving stories, following up the greatest cinematic cliffhanger since <em>The Empire Strikes Back</em>  was immense, which only makes it more miraculous that the Russo Brothers (and writers <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/christopher-markus/" target="_blank">Christopher Markus</a> &amp; Stephen McFeeley) delivered a thrilling, adventurous, emotional time-travelling trip through the entire MCU so far. The character pay-offs are just as staggering as the action  and when Steve Rogers finally proved worthy enough to lift Mjolnir, a stone-cold cultural moment was created.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/avengers-endgame-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Avengers: Endgame</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-79"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Alien" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b4d1/5909/d003/124c/88d5/21%20Alien.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b4d1/5909/d003/124c/88d5/21%20Alien.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b4d1/5909/d003/124c/88d5/21%20Alien.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b4d1/5909/d003/124c/88d5/21%20Alien.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b4d1/5909/d003/124c/88d5/21%20Alien.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b4d1/5909/d003/124c/88d5/21%20Alien.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">80<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">21) Alien</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>On the one hand, re-watching <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/ridley-scott/" target="_blank">Ridley Scott'</a>s deep-space monster-slasher (and it's a movie which can handle as many re-watches as you can throw at it) makes you appreciate why he keeps coming back to that universe: it's so intoxicatingly atmospheric and deeply compelling, it sticks to you like a parasite. On the other hand, it really does make you wonder why he feels the need to keep tinkering with new cuts. After all, he got it perfectly right the first time around.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/alien-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Alien</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-40"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-80"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Matrix" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b52d/5909/d0c1/974c/88da/20%20The%20Matrix.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b52d/5909/d0c1/974c/88da/20%20The%20Matrix.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b52d/5909/d0c1/974c/88da/20%20The%20Matrix.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b52d/5909/d0c1/974c/88da/20%20The%20Matrix.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b52d/5909/d0c1/974c/88da/20%20The%20Matrix.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b52d/5909/d0c1/974c/88da/20%20The%20Matrix.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">81<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">20) The Matrix</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>How two sibling indie film-makers with only a slick, sexy little crime film to their name (<em>Bound</em>) created their own blockbuster sci-fi franchise. And opened up western audiences to the truth that kung-fu acrobatics are so much more fun than watching American or European muscle-men waving guns around. While also making everyone examine some fundamental philosophical questions about reality. Thanks to the Wachowskis, we all took the red pill, and we've never regretted it.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/matrix-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Matrix</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-81"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Inception" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b56d/3ebe/473b/3c9c/e466/19%20Inception.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b56d/3ebe/473b/3c9c/e466/19%20Inception.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b56d/3ebe/473b/3c9c/e466/19%20Inception.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b56d/3ebe/473b/3c9c/e466/19%20Inception.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b56d/3ebe/473b/3c9c/e466/19%20Inception.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b56d/3ebe/473b/3c9c/e466/19%20Inception.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">82<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">19) Inception</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Will <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/christopher-nolan/" target="_blank">Christopher Nolan</a> ever make a Bond movie? Well, with Inception he kind of already has. Except, instead of a British secret agent, we get a freelance corporate dream-thief. And the big climactic action sequence is so huge it takes up almost half the movie and is actually three big action sequences temporally nested inside each other around a surreal, metaphysical-conflict core.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/inception-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Inception</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-41"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-82"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Parasite" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b5e4/f590/5e2c/2106/4978/18%20parasite.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b5e4/f590/5e2c/2106/4978/18%20parasite.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b5e4/f590/5e2c/2106/4978/18%20parasite.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b5e4/f590/5e2c/2106/4978/18%20parasite.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b5e4/f590/5e2c/2106/4978/18%20parasite.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b5e4/f590/5e2c/2106/4978/18%20parasite.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">83<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">18) Parasite</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Few award ceremony moments stick in the mind more than <em>Parasite</em> taking the Best Picture gong at the Oscars in 2020. It's no surprise that it made history as the first non-English language movie to do so  this South Korean genre-defying delight offers some of the biggest twists and expertly mounted tension in recent memory, with a family of excellent performances from <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/song-kang-ho/" target="_blank">Song Kang-ho</a>, Park So-dam, Choi Woo-shik and more. Bitingly satirical, darkly comedic and made with unmatched precision, <em>Parasite</em> doesn't just overcome the 'one inch barrier' of subtitles, as referenced in director <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/bong-joon-ho/" target="_blank">Bong Joon-ho</a>'s acceptance speech  it obliterates it entirely.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/parasite/">Read Empire's review of Parasite</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-83"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Aliens" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b6c6/5909/d0f9/124c/88e8/17%20Aliens.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b6c6/5909/d0f9/124c/88e8/17%20Aliens.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b6c6/5909/d0f9/124c/88e8/17%20Aliens.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b6c6/5909/d0f9/124c/88e8/17%20Aliens.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b6c6/5909/d0f9/124c/88e8/17%20Aliens.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b6c6/5909/d0f9/124c/88e8/17%20Aliens.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">84<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">17) Aliens</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>The genius of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/james-cameron/" target="_blank">James Cameron</a>'s self-penned <em>Alien</em> follow-up was to not try to top the original as one of the greatest ever horror movies. Instead, he transplanted the Alien (and, significantly, Ripley) to a different genre, and created one of the greatest ever action movies. That's also a Vietnam metaphor. And also one of the most enduringly quotable films.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/aliens-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Aliens</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-42"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-84"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Blade Runner" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b706/5165/4356/fc3b/7c4c/16%20Blade%20Runner.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b706/5165/4356/fc3b/7c4c/16%20Blade%20Runner.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b706/5165/4356/fc3b/7c4c/16%20Blade%20Runner.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b706/5165/4356/fc3b/7c4c/16%20Blade%20Runner.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b706/5165/4356/fc3b/7c4c/16%20Blade%20Runner.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b706/5165/4356/fc3b/7c4c/16%20Blade%20Runner.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">85<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">16) Blade Runner</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Rain-lashed, noodle-bar-packed streets shrouded in perpetual night, with giant adverts and neon signs doing the job you'd usually expect of the sun itself... The not-too-distant future had never looked cooler than in <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/ridley-scott/" target="_blank">Ridley Scott</a>'s sci-fi gumshoe noir, and we're not sure it ever will.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/blade-runner-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Blade Runner</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-85"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Jurassic Park" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b770/5165/430f/dc3b/7c52/15%20Jurassic%20Park.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b770/5165/430f/dc3b/7c52/15%20Jurassic%20Park.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b770/5165/430f/dc3b/7c52/15%20Jurassic%20Park.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b770/5165/430f/dc3b/7c52/15%20Jurassic%20Park.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b770/5165/430f/dc3b/7c52/15%20Jurassic%20Park.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b770/5165/430f/dc3b/7c52/15%20Jurassic%20Park.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">86<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">15) Jurassic Park</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>When dinosaurs first ruled the movie-Earth, they did so in a herky-jerky stop-motion manner that while charmingly effective, required a fair dose of disbelief-suspension. When <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/steven-spielberg/" target="_blank">Steven Spielberg</a> brought them back on Isla Nublar, we felt for the first time they could be real, breathing animals (as opposed to monsters). And that's as much thanks to <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/stan-winston/" target="_blank">Stan Winston</a>'s astonishing animatronics work as to ILM's groundbreaking CGI.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/jurassic-park-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Jurassic Park</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-43"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-86"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Godfather Part II" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b89c/dbee/afac/6469/00c1/14%20Godfather%202.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b89c/dbee/afac/6469/00c1/14%20Godfather%202.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b89c/dbee/afac/6469/00c1/14%20Godfather%202.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b89c/dbee/afac/6469/00c1/14%20Godfather%202.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b89c/dbee/afac/6469/00c1/14%20Godfather%202.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b89c/dbee/afac/6469/00c1/14%20Godfather%202.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">87<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">14) The Godfather Part II</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Often cited as the greatest-ever sequel, <em>TGPII</em>, as no-one's ever called it, is more accurately described as a seprequel. In a narrative masterstroke, it parallels Michael's (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/al-pacino/" target="_blank">Al Pacino</a>) consolidation of power with the ascendance of his Dad, Vito (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/robert-de-niro/" target="_blank">Robert De Niro</a>); the triumph of one paving the way to the utter corruption of the other.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/godfather-part-ii-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Godfather Part II</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-87"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Back To The Future" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b942/3ebe/473a/489c/e486/13%20BTTF.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b942/3ebe/473a/489c/e486/13%20BTTF.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b942/3ebe/473a/489c/e486/13%20BTTF.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b942/3ebe/473a/489c/e486/13%20BTTF.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b942/3ebe/473a/489c/e486/13%20BTTF.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b942/3ebe/473a/489c/e486/13%20BTTF.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">88<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">13) Back To The Future</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Part science-fiction caper, part generational culture-clash movie, part weirdo family drama (in which the hero has to rescue his own existence after his mother falls in lust with him, eww), <em>Back To The Future</em> still manages to be timeless despite being so rooted in, well, time. And it might just have the best title of anything on this entire list.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/back-future-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Back To The Future</a></p>
