</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-44"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-88"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Mad Max: Fury Road" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b97c/5165/43fb/d03b/7c65/12%20Fury%20Road.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b97c/5165/43fb/d03b/7c65/12%20Fury%20Road.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b97c/5165/43fb/d03b/7c65/12%20Fury%20Road.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b97c/5165/43fb/d03b/7c65/12%20Fury%20Road.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b97c/5165/43fb/d03b/7c65/12%20Fury%20Road.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b97c/5165/43fb/d03b/7c65/12%20Fury%20Road.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">89<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">12) Mad Max: Fury Road</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>In which old dog <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/george-miller/" target="_blank">George Miller</a> taught Hollywood some new tricks. Stripping the chase movie down to its raw essentials (the plot is basically: run away... then run back again!), Miller expertly built the narrative through some of the most astonishing and gloriously operatic action scenes we'd seen in yonks. While also ensuring his female characters are the film's strongest; <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/charlize-theron/" target="_blank">Charlize Theron</a>'s Furiosa and Immortan Joe's ex-brides are inheriting a world "killed" by men...<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/mad-max-fury-road-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Mad Max: Fury Road</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-89"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Star Wars" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b9f5/3ebe/477b/3f9c/e48a/11%20Star%20Wars.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b9f5/3ebe/477b/3f9c/e48a/11%20Star%20Wars.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b9f5/3ebe/477b/3f9c/e48a/11%20Star%20Wars.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b9f5/3ebe/477b/3f9c/e48a/11%20Star%20Wars.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b9f5/3ebe/477b/3f9c/e48a/11%20Star%20Wars.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/b9f5/3ebe/477b/3f9c/e48a/11%20Star%20Wars.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">90<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">11) Star Wars</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/george-lucas/" target="_blank">George Lucas</a>' cocktail of fantasy, sci-fi, Western and World War II movie remains as culturally pervasive as ever. It's so mythically potent, you sense in time it could become a bona-fide religion...</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/star-wars-episode-iv-new-hope-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Star Wars</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-45"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-90"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Goodfellas" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ba59/5165/43e0/333b/7c6f/10%20Goodfellas.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ba59/5165/43e0/333b/7c6f/10%20Goodfellas.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ba59/5165/43e0/333b/7c6f/10%20Goodfellas.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ba59/5165/43e0/333b/7c6f/10%20Goodfellas.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ba59/5165/43e0/333b/7c6f/10%20Goodfellas.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/ba59/5165/43e0/333b/7c6f/10%20Goodfellas.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">91<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">10) Goodfellas</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Where <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/francis-ford-coppola/" target="_blank">Coppola</a> embroiled us in the politics of the Mafia elite, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/martin-scorsese/" target="_blank">Martin Scorsese</a> drew us into the treacherous but seductive world of the Mob's foot soldiers. And its honesty was as impactful as its sudden outbursts of (usually <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/joe-pesci/" target="_blank">Joe Pesci</a>-instigated) violence. Not merely via Henry Hill's (<a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/ray-liotta/" target="_blank">Ray Liotta</a>) narrative, but also Karen's (Lorraine Bracco) perspective: when Henry gives her a gun to hide, she admits, "It turned me on."</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/goodfellas-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Goodfellas</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-91"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Raiders Of The Lost Ark" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bb13/f590/5e77/c706/49ac/9%20Raiders.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bb13/f590/5e77/c706/49ac/9%20Raiders.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bb13/f590/5e77/c706/49ac/9%20Raiders.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bb13/f590/5e77/c706/49ac/9%20Raiders.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bb13/f590/5e77/c706/49ac/9%20Raiders.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bb13/f590/5e77/c706/49ac/9%20Raiders.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">92<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">9) Raiders Of The Lost Ark</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>In '81, it must have sounded like the ultimate pitch: the creator of <em>Star Wars</em> teams up with the director of <em>Jaws</em> to make a rip-roaring, Bond-style adventure starring the guy who played Han Solo, in which the bad guys are the evillest ever (the Nazis) and the MacGuffin is a big, gold box which unleashes the power of God. It still sounds like the ultimate pitch.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/raiders-lost-ark-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Raiders Of The Lost Ark</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-46"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-92"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Avengers: Infinity War" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bb98/3ebe/4758/9d9c/e49e/8%20Infinity%20War.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bb98/3ebe/4758/9d9c/e49e/8%20Infinity%20War.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bb98/3ebe/4758/9d9c/e49e/8%20Infinity%20War.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bb98/3ebe/4758/9d9c/e49e/8%20Infinity%20War.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bb98/3ebe/4758/9d9c/e49e/8%20Infinity%20War.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bb98/3ebe/4758/9d9c/e49e/8%20Infinity%20War.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">93<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">8) Avengers: Infinity War</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>It was the biggest crossover event in cinematic history, and the biggest cliffhanger we never saw coming. After ten years and eighteen movies, Marvel took superhero filmmaking to a new level when they united all of Earth's mightiest heroes (and several more) against The Mad Titan himself  and incredibly, devastatingly, they lost. <em>Infinity War</em> crashed much-loved characters into each other's orbits, flitting between planets at breakneck speed as the Avengers desperately tried to stop Thanos from clicking his fingers and wiping out half the universe. Spectacular action, punch-the-air moments and big-scale battles are perfectly balanced, as all things should be, with hilarious interplays and aching emotion. Cinema doesn't get much bigger, or better, than this.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/avengers-infinity-war-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Avengers: Infinity War</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-93"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Pulp Fiction" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bc1a/5909/d0f3/1e4c/890c/7%20Pulp%20Fiction.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bc1a/5909/d0f3/1e4c/890c/7%20Pulp%20Fiction.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bc1a/5909/d0f3/1e4c/890c/7%20Pulp%20Fiction.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bc1a/5909/d0f3/1e4c/890c/7%20Pulp%20Fiction.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bc1a/5909/d0f3/1e4c/890c/7%20Pulp%20Fiction.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bc1a/5909/d0f3/1e4c/890c/7%20Pulp%20Fiction.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">94<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">7) Pulp Fiction</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>If <em>Reservoir Dogs</em> was a blood-spattered calling card, <em>Pulp Fiction</em> saw <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/quentin-tarantino/" target="_blank">Quentin Tarantino</a> kick our front door off its hinges  and then get applauded for doing it with such goddamn panache. It wore its numerous influences on its sleeve and yet felt utterly, invigoratingly fresh and new. We happy? Yeah, we happy.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/pulp-fiction-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Pulp Fiction</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-47"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-94"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Jaws" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bc72/3ebe/47f1/829c/e4a1/6%20Jaws.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bc72/3ebe/47f1/829c/e4a1/6%20Jaws.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bc72/3ebe/47f1/829c/e4a1/6%20Jaws.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bc72/3ebe/47f1/829c/e4a1/6%20Jaws.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bc72/3ebe/47f1/829c/e4a1/6%20Jaws.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bc72/3ebe/47f1/829c/e4a1/6%20Jaws.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">95<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">6) Jaws</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Forty-five years young, and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/steven-spielberg/" target="_blank">Spielberg</a>'s breakthrough remains the touchstone for event-movie cinema. Not that any studio these days would dare put out a summer blockbuster that's half monster-on-the-rampage disaster, half guys-bonding-on-a-fishing-trip adventure. Maybe that's why it's never been rebooted. Or just because it's genuinely unsurpassable.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/jaws-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of Jaws</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-95"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Shawshank Redemption" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bcdd/5165/4383/223b/7c83/5%20Shawshank.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bcdd/5165/4383/223b/7c83/5%20Shawshank.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bcdd/5165/4383/223b/7c83/5%20Shawshank.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bcdd/5165/4383/223b/7c83/5%20Shawshank.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bcdd/5165/4383/223b/7c83/5%20Shawshank.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bcdd/5165/4383/223b/7c83/5%20Shawshank.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">96<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">5) The Shawshank Redemption</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>The warm, leathery embrace of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/morgan-freeman/" target="_blank">Morgan Freeman</a>'s narration... The reassuringly <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/gary-cooper/" target="_blank">Gary Cooper</a>-ish rumple of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/tim-robbins/" target="_blank">Tim Robbins</a>' face... Odd that a movie which features such harshness and tragedy should remain a feel-good perennial  even odder when you consider it was a box-office flop on release. Few directorial debuts are so deftly constructed; no surprise, then, that <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/frank-darabont/" target="_blank">Frank Darabont</a> has yet to top it.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/shawshank-redemption-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Shawshank Redemption</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-48"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-96"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Dark Knight" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bd81/3ebe/47b5/fa9c/e4ac/4%20dark%20knight.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bd81/3ebe/47b5/fa9c/e4ac/4%20dark%20knight.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bd81/3ebe/47b5/fa9c/e4ac/4%20dark%20knight.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bd81/3ebe/47b5/fa9c/e4ac/4%20dark%20knight.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bd81/3ebe/47b5/fa9c/e4ac/4%20dark%20knight.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bd81/3ebe/47b5/fa9c/e4ac/4%20dark%20knight.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">97<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">4) The Dark Knight</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>Easily as influential on the genre as that other summer '08 comic-book movie, <em>Iron Man</em>, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/christopher-nolan/" target="_blank">Christopher Nolan</a>'s <em>Batman Begins</em> sequel works wonders because he never saw it as a superhero film. It's closer to a <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/michael-mann/" target="_blank">Michael Mann</a> crime epic  except instead of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/al-pacino/" target="_blank">Pacino</a> and <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/robert-de-niro/" target="_blank">De Niro</a> in a diner, you get a bloke dressed as a bat and a psychotic clown in a police interrogation room. With, er, <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/aaron-eckhart/" target="_blank">Aaron Eckhart</a> as <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/val-kilmer/" target="_blank">Val Kilmer</a>...</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/dark-knight-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Dark Knight</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-97"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Godfather" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/be32/5165/433b/cc3b/7c8f/3%20Godfather.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/be32/5165/433b/cc3b/7c8f/3%20Godfather.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/be32/5165/433b/cc3b/7c8f/3%20Godfather.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/be32/5165/433b/cc3b/7c8f/3%20Godfather.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/be32/5165/433b/cc3b/7c8f/3%20Godfather.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/be32/5165/433b/cc3b/7c8f/3%20Godfather.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">98<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">3) The Godfather</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/stanley-kubrick/" target="_blank">Stanley Kubrick</a> once described <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/francis-ford-coppola/" target="_blank">Francis Ford Coppola</a>'s adaptation of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/mario-puzo/" target="_blank">Mario Puzo</a>'s novel as the best film ever made  though having previously topped this list, this time it falls to bronze position. At once an art movie and a commercial blockbuster, <em>The Godfather</em> marked the dawn of the age of the mega-movie. An icon of the gangster genre, its imprinted in popular culture  "Luca Brasi sleeps with the fishes", the horse's head in the bed  but the first instalment of Brando's cotton-cheeked patriarch's fight for power is so much more than those moments. With performances, style and substance to savour, it's managed to both smash box office records and live on as a staple of cinematic canon.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/godfather-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Godfather</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-49"></div></div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-98"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bf59/3ebe/4721/a59c/e4be/2%20ESB.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bf59/3ebe/4721/a59c/e4be/2%20ESB.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bf59/3ebe/4721/a59c/e4be/2%20ESB.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bf59/3ebe/4721/a59c/e4be/2%20ESB.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bf59/3ebe/4721/a59c/e4be/2%20ESB.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bf59/3ebe/4721/a59c/e4be/2%20ESB.jpg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">99<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">2) Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>The original "this one's darker" sequel, and by far the strongest of the saga. Not just because the baddies win (temporarily), or because it Force-slammed us with that twist ("No, I am your father"). Empire super-stardestroys thanks to the way it deepens the core relationships  none more effectively than Han and Leia's. She loves him. He knows. And it still hurts.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/star-wars-episode-v-empire-strikes-back-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Empire Strikes Back</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__item__OCDTx" data-test="listicle-item-99"><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__image__EWbyD"><img alt="The Lord Of The Rings: The Fellowship Of The Ring" data-nimg="fill" decoding="async" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw,48vw" src="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bfe9/5909/d08f/544c/892d/1%20Fellowship.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80" srcset="https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bfe9/5909/d08f/544c/892d/1%20Fellowship.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=480&amp;q=80 480w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bfe9/5909/d08f/544c/892d/1%20Fellowship.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=768&amp;q=80 768w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bfe9/5909/d08f/544c/892d/1%20Fellowship.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=992&amp;q=80 992w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bfe9/5909/d08f/544c/892d/1%20Fellowship.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1200&amp;q=80 1200w, https://images.bauerhosting.com/legacy/media/619d/bfe9/5909/d08f/544c/892d/1%20Fellowship.jpeg?auto=format&amp;w=1440&amp;q=80 1440w" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http%3A//www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cimage style='filter:blur(20px)' x='0' y='0' height='100%25' width='100%25' href='data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mO8/B8AAqsB1DKTUZgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='/%3E%3C/svg%3E&quot;)"/><span class="listicleItem_listicle-item__count__9dJzP">100<!-- --> of <!-- -->100</span></div><h3 class="listicleItem_listicle-item__title__hW_Kn">1) The Lord Of The Rings: The Fellowship Of The Ring</h3><div class="listicleItem_listicle-item__content__cDxdR">
<p>A wizard is never late. Nor is he early. He arrives precisely when he... well, you know the rest. It might have taken 20 years for <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/peter-jackson/" target="_blank">Peter Jackson</a>'s plucky fantasy to clamber, Mount-Doom-style, to the very pinnacle of our greatest-movies pantheon. But here it is, brighter and more resplendent than ever.<em>The Fellowship Of The Ring</em> contains so much movie. Even at the halfway point, as the characters take a breather to bicker in Rivendell, you already feel sated, like you've experienced more thrills, more suspense, more jollity and ethereal beauty than a regular film could possibly muster up. But Jackson is only getting started. Onwards his adventure hustles, to the bravura dungeoneering of Khazad-dum, to the sinisterly serene glades of Lothlorien, to the final requiem for flawed Boromir amidst autumnal leaves. As <em>Fellowship</em> thrums to its conclusion, finally applying the brakes with a last swell of <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/people/howard-shore/" target="_blank">Howard Shore</a>'s heavenly score, you're left feeling euphoric, bereft and hopeful, all at the same time. <em>The Two Towers</em> has the coolest battle. <em>The Return Of The King</em> boasts the most batshit, operatic spectacle. But Fellowship remains the most perfect of the three, matching every genius action beat with a soul-stirring emotional one, as its Middle-earth-traversing gang swells in size in the first act, then dwindles in the third. This oddball suicide squad has so much warmth and wit, they're not just believable as friends of each other  they've come to feel like they're our pals too.An ornately detailed masterwork with a huge, pulsing heart, it's just the right film for our times  full of craft, conviction and a belief that trudging forward, step by step, in dark days is the bravest act of all. Its ultimate heroes aren't the strongest, or those with the best one-liners, but the ones who just keep going. And so <em>Fellowship</em> endures: a miracle of storytelling, a feat of filmmaking and still the gold standard for cinematic experiences. Right, now that's decided, who's up for second breakfast?</p>
<p><a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/lord-rings-fellowship-ring-review/" target="_blank">Read Empire's review of The Lord Of The Rings: The Fellowship Of The Ring</a></p>
</div></div><div class="listicle_listicle__adWrapper__J6amM"><div><div class="advert_advert__PDEAw" id="inline-mpu-gallery-50"></div></div></div></div><span class="content_content__ibcyj" data-test="content">

But here it is, brighter and more resplendent than ever._The Fellowship Of The Ring_ contains so much movie. Even at the halfway point, as the characters take a breather to bicker in Rivendell, you already feel sated, like you've experienced more thrills, more suspense, more jollity and ethereal beauty than a regular film could possibly muster up. Onwards his adventure hustles, to the bravura dungeoneering of Khazad-dum, to the sinisterly serene glades of Lothlorien, to the final requiem for flawed Boromir amidst autumnal leaves. As _Fellowship_ thrums to its conclusion, finally applying the brakes with a last swell of :a[Howard Shore]{href='https://www.empireonline.com/people/howard-shore/' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'}'s heavenly score, you're left feeling euphoric, bereft and hopeful, all at the same time. _The Two Towers_ has the coolest battle. _The Return Of The King_ boasts the most batshit, operatic spectacle. But Fellowship remains the most perfect of the three, matching every genius action beat with a soul-stirring emotional one, as its Middle-earth-traversing gang swells in size in the first act, then dwindles in the third. This oddball suicide squad has so much warmth and wit, they're not just believable as friends of each other  they've come to feel like they're our pals too.An ornately detailed masterwork with a huge, pulsing heart, it's just the right film for our times  full of craft, conviction and a belief that trudging forward, step by step, in dark days is the bravest act of all. Its ultimate heroes aren't the strongest, or those with the best one-liners, but the ones who just keep going. And so _Fellowship_ endures: a miracle of storytelling, a feat of filmmaking and still the gold standard for cinematic experiences. # Extracting the all text data and creating list:

extracted_text = []

# Loop through the ResultSet and extract text from the Tag objects
for tag in movie_list:
    text = tag.get_text().strip()
    extracted_text.append(text)

In [12]:
# Creating a function for removing pstarting_digits_and_parentheses with the help of regular expression:

def remove_starting_digits_and_parentheses(item):
    # Use regular expressions to remove starting digits and any text within parentheses
    cleaned_item = re.sub(r'^\d+\)\s*', '', item).strip()
    return cleaned_item
In [13]:
# Applying function as we can see difference:

df['The 100 Best Movies Of All Time'] = df['The 100 Best Movies Of All Time'].apply(remove_starting_digits_and_parentheses)

# Print the DataFrame
print(df)

# Arranging dataframe into ascending order by help with Rank:

# Sort the DataFrame in ascending order by the 'Rank' column
df = df.sort_values(by='Rank', ascending=False)

# Reset the index
df.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)

# Print the sorted DataFrame
print(df)
